// Auto-generated from SME_Lending_Head_of_Product_Strategy (2).docx
// Includes paragraphs, lists, headings, AND tables. Do not edit by hand.
window.MAL_STRATEGY_DOC = [{"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "Head of Product Strategy", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "UAE SME Lending Platform", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "Three Differentiated Products", "b": false, "i": true}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "End-to-End Product Manager Workflow", "b": false, "i": true}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "Three-Year Unit Economics", "b": false, "i": true}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Confidential. Internal. Working Draft.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "May 2026", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "1. Executive Overview", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "1-executive-overview", "text": "1. Executive Overview"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "UAE SMEs are 94 percent of all enterprises, contribute roughly 40 percent of GDP and 63 percent of non-oil GDP, and employ over 40 percent of the workforce. Despite that, only 28 percent have ever accessed bank credit and SME lending sits at 9.5 percent of total commercial bank facilities. The MENA SME finance gap runs at 88 percent of demand, the highest of any region. The cause is structural: suppliers want their cash on day one, corporate buyers pay in 60 to 90 days, peak-season inventory is bought upfront, and bank approvals take four to eight weeks. The opportunity has usually moved on by the time credit clears.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The middle of the market is empty. Traditional banks are slow, demand collateral, and run annual review cycles built for corporates, not for SMEs. Fintechs (Beehive, CredibleX, Funding Souq, Comfi, Klaim and a handful of others) are fast but expensive — pricing sits at 18 to 30 percent per annum where bank-grade credit sits at 10 to 18 percent. Nobody serves the SME with bank-cost capital and digital-native speed. There is also no end-to-end Sharia-compliant SME lender online — Islamic SME credit still runs through branch processes at DIB, ADIB and Emirates Islamic. Roughly half of UAE SME owners would prefer or require Sharia structuring.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "MAL is built to close that middle. Lower cost of funds than fintechs, faster decisions and digital-only servicing than banks, and Sharia-compliant by default through Tawarruq and Wakala structures so the same product serves both segments without separate SKUs. The platform sits on top of the data infrastructure that the UAE has spent the last three years putting in place: CBUAE Open Finance and the Nebras API Hub for cash-flow data, the federal e-invoicing mandate (pilot July 2026, full SME coverage by July 2027) for verified receivables, AECB credit bureau coverage for repayment history, and POS / payment-processor data through partners like Network International and Magnati for live revenue signals. The lender that builds underwriting models on this stack first has a structural advantage — the closest analogue is India's GST rollout, which took digital SME loan disbursements up 12x in three years.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This document picks three SME lending products that ride exactly that wave and lays out the full product manager view of each. For every product we cover what it solves, who it serves, the buyer and supplier journeys, the origination and servicing operations, the collections playbook, the technology stack, the API contracts, the OCR and verification flow, the Sharia variant, and the three-year unit economics.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The three products picked are:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Product 1: Smart Invoice with Flexible Installment B2B Buy Now Pay Later. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "One workflow clears one invoice. The supplier gets paid on day one at 90 to 95 percent advance. The buyer chooses to settle in 30, 60, 90 days, or in 2 to 6 monthly instalments. The installment option is the differentiator versus Comfi, Beehive, Funding Souq, eFunder, Aura, and Zelo.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Product 2: Healthcare Insurance Receivables Engine. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Buys claims from clinics, polyclinics, day-surgery centres, dental groups and pharmacies the same day. Replaces the 60 to 112 day insurer settlement cycle. Differentiator versus Klaim is multi-payer aggregation, machine-learning claim adjudication, and a Sharia asset-backed structure that works at fund scale.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Product 3: Anchor-Led Supply Chain Finance with Dynamic Discount. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Reverse factoring against approved-payable invoices from a panel of large UAE anchors. The differentiator is a daily auction window where suppliers can bid for an earlier payment date at a steeper discount, capturing the spread that anchors and traditional banks today pocket as float.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Each of these products is timed to a structural ecosystem shift in the UAE. The federal e-invoicing mandate goes live in pilot from July 2026, mandatory for large taxpayers from January 2027, and mandatory for SMEs from July 2027. CBUAE Open Finance Regulation Circular 3 of 2025 has been in force since 10 July 2025, with Lean Technologies as the first In-Principle Approval holder. The Emirates Development Bank credit guarantee scheme is live with 13 partner banks and AED 1.58 billion deployed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Together these create the data, identity and risk-sharing rails on which the three products run. Without them, two of the three products would be uneconomic. With them, all three are AED 1 billion plus opportunities within three years.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "1.1 Combined Three-Year Outlook", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "1-1-combined-three-year-outlook", "text": "1.1 Combined Three-Year Outlook"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Volume disbursed across the three products:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "650", "3,500", "10,000"], ["Avg. Outstanding Book (AED M)", "220", "1,200", "3,450"], ["Active SME Customers", "1,500", "8,500", "22,000"], ["Active Anchor / Insurer Partners", "5", "12", "20"], ["Gross Yield (blended)", "18.0%", "16.5%", "15.0%"], ["Cost of Funds (blended)", "8.8%", "8.3%", "7.8%"], ["Net Interest Margin", "9.2%", "8.2%", "7.2%"], ["Provision for Credit Loss", "1.8%", "1.7%", "1.6%"], ["Risk-Adjusted Margin", "7.4%", "6.5%", "5.6%"], ["Operating Expenses (% of book)", "5.0%", "3.2%", "2.4%"], ["Net Contribution (% of book)", "2.4%", "3.3%", "3.2%"], ["Net Contribution (AED M)", "5.3", "39.6", "110.4"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Capital plan to support this trajectory: USD 75 to 100 million senior warehouse from a private credit fund (Pollen Street, Channel Capital, Stride Ventures, EBRD, IFC); USD 20 to 30 million mezzanine from regional family offices; equity capital sufficient to cover Year 1 to Year 2 burn plus regulatory minimum capital requirements.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "2. Platform Context and Foundations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "2-platform-context-and-foundations", "text": "2. Platform Context and Foundations"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The three products share a common platform stack. We build the stack once and reuse it across products. This section sets out what that stack must do before any individual product can ship.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "2.1 Foundational Capabilities", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "2-1-foundational-capabilities", "text": "2.1 Foundational Capabilities"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Five capabilities sit at the centre of the platform. Each must be live, tested, and operating at SLA before a product launches in production.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Capability", "What It Does", "Vendor / Build", "SLA"], ["Identity and KYB", "Verifies trade licence, UBO, signatories, sanctions; assigns customer ID", "UAE Pass, Sumsub, Refinitiv, Dow Jones; ASP partner for FTA TRN check", "5 minutes for clean files; 4 hours for review queue"], ["Open Finance Data", "Pulls 12 months bank statements, account list, balances, transactions", "Lean Technologies (primary); Tarabut (secondary)", "30 seconds for first pull; 60 minutes for refresh"], ["Credit Bureau", "Pulls AECB Commercial Credit Report and Score; cheque clearance flag", "Al Etihad Credit Bureau (Etihad Bureau App API)", "10 seconds"], ["Peppol e-Invoice", "Receives, validates, parses Peppol PINT AE invoices", "Accredited Service Provider (Avalara, Pagero, Comarch, Tradeshift, RTC)", "60 seconds from issuance to dashboard"], ["Direct Debit and Payment Initiation", "Pulls money from buyer; pushes money to supplier; reconciles", "Lean PIS; UAEFTS for high-value; bank IPP for instant payments", "Same-day for credits; T+0 for debits"], ["Decisioning Engine", "Runs scorecard, policy rules, exception flags; outputs decision and limit", "In-house build on Python, XGBoost, Feast feature store", "5 seconds for scoring; 5 minutes end-to-end"], ["Loan Management System", "Books, accruals, schedules, statements, fees, repayments, write-offs", "Mambu cloud (recommended); fallback Finflux or in-house", "99.9% uptime"], ["Document and OCR", "Captures invoice PDFs, screenshots, photos; structures fields", "AWS Textract + Layoutlmv3 fine-tune for Phase 1; Peppol XML for Phase 2", "10 seconds per document"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "2.2 Operating Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "2-2-operating-model", "text": "2.2 Operating Model"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Run the platform with a tight team of high-agency operators, not a department. The default is fewer people, more leverage — every member is expected to think from first principles, ship in days not quarters, and use AI as a force multiplier on research, design, code review, credit memos and ops. The throughput target is at least three times the benchmark for a comparable lender, achieved through compounding small productivity wins (instrument every flow, kill every recurring meeting that AI can absorb, automate every internal write-up before hiring around it).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The risk model is the platform's centre of gravity, owned by the CRO and not by product. Product teams own the experience that delivers risk decisions to the customer; risk owns the model itself, the policy, the watchlist and the vintage cohorts. A weekly Credit Forum chaired by the CRO is where new products, anchors, verticals and policy moves get debated and signed off — product brings the customer story, risk brings the data, and the forum decides. The principle is small-team density: a single staff engineer carrying platform, two designers covering buyer and supplier journeys end-to-end, one product lead per product line, all close enough to the credit data that nobody is decoding it second-hand.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "3. Product 1: Smart Invoice with Flexible Installment B2B BNPL", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-product-1-smart-invoice-with-flexible-installmen", "text": "3. Product 1: Smart Invoice with Flexible Installment B2B BNPL"}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.1 Product Thesis", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-1-product-thesis", "text": "3.1 Product Thesis"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "A typical UAE SME pays its suppliers on 60 to 90 day terms. The supplier wants the cash now. The buyer wants to spread the outflow. Existing players solve only one side. Comfi serves the buyer with 30 / 60 / 90 day BNPL but does not pay the supplier on day one. Beehive, Funding Souq, eFunder, Aura, Zelo and Comfi-as-discounter serve the supplier with single-invoice discounting but do not give the buyer choice over how to repay. Banks serve neither side digitally for tickets under AED 500K.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This product clears one invoice in one workflow. The supplier gets paid in four hours at 90 to 95 percent advance. The buyer chooses the repayment plan. Both sides see the same invoice number, the same amount, the same due date, the same audit trail. The instalment option for the buyer is the headline differentiator. No competitor in the UAE today gives a buyer the choice to settle one invoice over six monthly instalments at a competitive rate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.2 Target Segments", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-2-target-segments", "text": "3.2 Target Segments"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Supplier side", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "supplier-side", "text": "Supplier side"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Trading SMEs in DMCC, JAFZA, IFZA, DMC, RAKEZ selling to mainland UAE buyers on net 30 to net 90 terms.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Service SMEs in marketing, IT services, recruitment, F&B supply, equipment maintenance, professional services.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Light manufacturers selling FMCG inputs, packaging, building materials, MEP and HVAC components.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Free-zone consultancies invoicing local clients in AED.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Annual turnover band: AED 2 million to AED 100 million. Operating account at any UAE bank reachable through Lean Open Finance.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Buyer side", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "buyer-side", "text": "Buyer side"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Mid-market SMEs and corporates with monthly purchase volume AED 100K to AED 5M.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Family businesses with multiple trading entities under one group.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Healthcare groups buying medical consumables and IT services.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Construction main contractors paying sub-contractors and suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Hospitality groups paying F&B and laundry suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Government contractors paying their own suppliers (downstream of slow government payments).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.3 The Buyer Journey End-to-End", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-3-the-buyer-journey-end-to-end", "text": "3.3 The Buyer Journey End-to-End"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 1: Onboarding", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-1-onboarding", "text": "Step 1: Onboarding"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Buyer downloads the app or visits the web portal. Hits a single button: \"Start in 5 minutes\".", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Authenticates via UAE Pass. App receives the OIDC token.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls trade licence from DET, DED, ADGM, or DIFC API on the back of the licence number entered.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls UBO and shareholder data from the Ministry of Economy registry.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls AECB Commercial Credit Report and Credit Score (300 to 900).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System asks buyer to consent to 12 months of bank statements via Lean. Buyer is shown the Lean consent flow, picks the bank, completes the strong customer authentication on the bank's app, and returns.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls VAT certificate and last four VAT returns from the FTA API.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls e-invoicing registration status from the FTA Peppol register.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Underwriting engine runs. Result in 60 seconds for clean files; up to 24 hours for review queue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 2: Limit Assignment", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-2-limit-assignment", "text": "Step 2: Limit Assignment"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Decisioning engine returns: limit between AED 50K and AED 5M; eligible repayment plans (which of 30/60/90/installments are open); fee tier.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit is shelved. The buyer does not need to use it today. It is simply available against any future invoice issued by a registered supplier.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit auto-refreshes monthly using a rolling 90-day bank statement view and Peppol invoice flow.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit can be increased on request after three months of clean repayment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 3: Invoice Lands in Buyer Dashboard", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-3-invoice-lands-in-buyer-dashboard", "text": "Step 3: Invoice Lands in Buyer Dashboard"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier issues an e-invoice to the buyer's TRN through any Accredited Service Provider on the Peppol network.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Our platform receives the Peppol document via the ASP partner and validates it against FTA records.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Invoice appears in buyer dashboard within 60 seconds of issuance.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Buyer is notified by push notification and email.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 4: Buyer Picks a Repayment Plan", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-4-buyer-picks-a-repayment-plan", "text": "Step 4: Buyer Picks a Repayment Plan"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "For each invoice the buyer sees five options on a single screen:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Plan", "Buyer Pays", "Fee (Conventional)", "Fee (Sharia / Tawarruq Profit)", "Differentiator"], ["Pay supplier directly", "Net term agreed with supplier", "0%", "0%", "No financing involved"], ["BNPL 30 days", "30 days from invoice date", "1.0% to 1.5%", "1.0% to 1.5% profit", "Equivalent to Comfi"], ["BNPL 60 days", "60 days from invoice date", "1.8% to 2.6%", "1.8% to 2.6% profit", "Equivalent to Comfi"], ["BNPL 90 days", "90 days from invoice date", "2.6% to 3.6%", "2.6% to 3.6% profit", "Equivalent to Comfi"], ["Installments (2 to 6)", "Equal monthly payments", "1.0% to 1.5% per 30 days", "Same profit rate, fixed schedule", "No UAE competitor today"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Pricing is risk-tiered. Tier A (AECB 720 plus, low DPD, strong cash flow): bottom of each band. Tier B: middle. Tier C (AECB 580-680, marginal cash flow, EDB-guarantee eligible): top of band, may require limited collateral. Tier D: declined or referred to anchor SCF.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 5: Buyer Confirms", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-5-buyer-confirms", "text": "Step 5: Buyer Confirms"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Two-factor confirmation through UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Direct-debit mandate set on the buyer's primary bank account through Open Finance Service Initiation. Mandate covers each scheduled instalment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Optional secondary post-dated cheque if the buyer is not on a Lean-connected bank. Targeted to be phased out by end-2027 as Open Finance coverage approaches 100 percent.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "For Sharia variant: an additional Tawarruq commodity transaction screen records the LME commodity purchase and immediate sale instructions. Standard fatwa-approved language is auto-populated.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 6: Repayment and Servicing", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-6-repayment-and-servicing", "text": "Step 6: Repayment and Servicing"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Auto-debit on each due date. Successful debit settles the instalment. Statement updated.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Push notification 7 days before due, 3 days before, 1 day before, and on the day.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "One-tap reschedule available twice in any rolling 12-month period. Each reschedule extends the date by up to 7 days at a 0.5 percent fee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "If a debit fails, the system retries at 11 am, 2 pm, 5 pm on the same day before triggering Day 1 collections.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.4 The Supplier Journey End-to-End", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-4-the-supplier-journey-end-to-end", "text": "3.4 The Supplier Journey End-to-End"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 1: Onboarding", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-1-onboarding-2", "text": "Step 1: Onboarding"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Same data spine as buyer onboarding: UAE Pass, trade licence APIs, AECB, Lean, FTA, MOET UBO.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Additional: bank account verification by penny-drop or by Lean account-information confirmation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Additional: cheque book held / no cheque book held flag.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Additional: counterparty list. Supplier confirms the names of their top 20 buyers. The system pre-flags which of these are already onboarded as buyer customers (lower risk) and which need a one-time KYB at the time of first financing (higher friction).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 2: Invoice Issuance and Discount", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-2-invoice-issuance-and-discount", "text": "Step 2: Invoice Issuance and Discount"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier issues the e-invoice through any ASP. Our platform receives the validated document and pulls structured fields automatically.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier dashboard shows: gross invoice value, the buyer credit grade, applicable advance rate (90 to 95 percent), applicable discount rate, expected net amount payable on day one.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Discount rate is built up from: cost of funds, buyer credit, tenor, recourse mode, sector premium, fraud check.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier picks recourse (1.0 to 1.8 percent per 30 days) or non-recourse (1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "One-tap accept. Funds are wired to the supplier's verified bank account within 4 hours; 24 hours is the SLA backstop.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 3: Receivable Assignment", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-3-receivable-assignment", "text": "Step 3: Receivable Assignment"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Notice of assignment is sent to the buyer through Peppol and email if the buyer is not yet on our platform (disclosed factoring).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Confidential mode runs where the buyer is on our platform: the buyer simply sees the invoice in their dashboard with our IBAN as the payment destination. From the buyer's perspective they pay the supplier through us. The supplier is paid by us upfront. The financial substance is identical; the buyer is none the wiser, and the supplier preserves their commercial relationship.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 4: Reconciliation", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-4-reconciliation", "text": "Step 4: Reconciliation"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "When the buyer settles, our platform receives the cash to its segregated client account.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System splits cash to the supplier (any retention, e.g. the 5 to 10 percent not advanced) and to the platform (principal plus discount).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier sees real-time receivable status: open, financed, paid, overdue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier statement is delivered monthly and on demand.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.5 OCR and Invoice Verification", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-5-ocr-and-invoice-verification", "text": "3.5 OCR and Invoice Verification"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "From day one we run a hybrid model. From July 2027 we expect Peppol to be the dominant channel and OCR a fallback only.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Phase 1: July 2026 to July 2027", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "phase-1-july-2026-to-july-2027", "text": "Phase 1: July 2026 to July 2027"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Document layer: AWS Textract for primary OCR; Google Document AI as fallback.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Field extraction: Layoutlmv3 fine-tuned on a UAE VAT invoice corpus of 50,000 labelled invoices in Arabic and English.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Required fields: TRN of supplier, TRN of buyer, invoice number, invoice date, due date, gross amount, VAT, net amount, line items, currency, IBAN of supplier.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cross-checks: TRN against FTA register; invoice number against duplicate-pledge database (we keep a hash of every invoice ever financed); supplier-buyer pair against historical pattern; IBAN against bank account ownership confirmed via Lean.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anti-fraud signals: Benford's Law analysis on amounts (flag stack of round numbers); image forensics for tampering (Photoshop signatures, font substitution); embedded font check for screenshot-edited invoices; reverse image search on invoice header.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human review queue: any invoice flagged by two or more anti-fraud signals; any first-time supplier-buyer pair above AED 250K; any invoice above AED 1M regardless of pair.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Phase 2: July 2027 onward", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "phase-2-july-2027-onward", "text": "Phase 2: July 2027 onward"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "All in-scope invoices are Peppol-validated. Our platform consumes the structured XML directly. Authenticity is given.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anti-fraud is reduced to: duplicate-pledge detection (still essential, as the same invoice can be pledged on two platforms); behavioural anomaly detection (sudden 10x rise in invoice volume from a supplier); buyer collusion detection (round-trip invoicing within an ownership cluster).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "OCR is retained as a fallback for non-Peppol documents (e.g. credit notes, proforma invoices, supporting documents) and for cross-border invoices.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.6 Risk Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-6-risk-model", "text": "3.6 Risk Model"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Supplier risk", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "supplier-risk", "text": "Supplier risk"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Recourse mode: supplier is the primary credit. Probability of default modelled from AECB Commercial Score, debt service coverage ratio from bank statement, cheque bounce history, sector code, age of business, ownership concentration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Non-recourse mode: buyer is the primary credit. Supplier risk reduced to fraud risk and dilution risk (the risk that the buyer raises a commercial dispute that reduces the receivable).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Buyer risk", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "buyer-risk", "text": "Buyer risk"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "AECB Commercial Credit Score is the primary input.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Open Finance signal: monthly inflow, monthly outflow, ending balance volatility, salary outflow consistency, returned-cheque frequency.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "E-invoicing flow signal: total VAT-invoiced last 12 months, supplier diversity, anchor-buyer relationships.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sector and business-age premium.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "WPS-linked employer signal where the buyer is also the WPS employer of one of our other customers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Concentration limits", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "concentration-limits", "text": "Concentration limits"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 5 percent of book to any single buyer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 10 percent of book to any single sector (trading, services, contracting, healthcare, F&B etc.).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 25 percent of book to any single anchor buyer where SCF anchor relationship overlaps.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 15 percent of book in non-recourse mode in Year 1, rising to 30 percent by Year 3.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.7 Servicing Operations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-7-servicing-operations", "text": "3.7 Servicing Operations"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Daily operations are automation-first.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Auto-reconciliation: bank inbound feed via Open Finance is polled every 15 minutes. Each credit is matched to an invoice using buyer TRN and remittance reference.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Mismatched payments are routed to an ops queue with a 4-hour SLA.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier dashboard refreshes every 15 minutes: financed, pending, overdue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Buyer dashboard shows outstanding, next due, available limit, recent activity, and a single button \"Pay early\" that triggers an Open Finance payment initiation against the buyer's connected bank.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Customer support runs 24/7 via Arabic and English chatbot for first response, with a 16-hour human window for escalation. Tickets above AED 500K route to a senior agent within 30 minutes.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.8 Collections Playbook", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-8-collections-playbook", "text": "3.8 Collections Playbook"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Stage", "Days Past Due", "Action", "Outcome / Escalation"], ["Soft", "1 to 4", "Auto SMS, email, push, in-app reminders. One-tap reschedule available.", "Most cures here. Pricing penalty 0.5%."], ["Tele-call", "5 to 14", "Human collections call. Settlement options: full repay, structured catch-up, roll into new instalment plan with 2% penalty.", "Soft restructure if cash flow shock; field visit if no contact."], ["Field and notice", "15 to 30", "Supervisor escalation. Registered notice via courier. AECB negative reporting initiated.", "Letter response or partial pay; if no response, legal pre-action."], ["Legal", "31 to 60", "Legal demand letter. Cheque deposit if applicable (police case under cheque law).", "Settlement under threat of police case is common in this window."], ["Recovery / Sale", "61 to 90", "Najiz / DIFC small claims; sale to recovery partner at 30 to 60 cents on the dirham; charge-off after 90.", "Recovery partner: Falcon Recovery, ADRC, or in-house"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.9 Technology Stack", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-9-technology-stack", "text": "3.9 Technology Stack"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Build versus buy decisions are made on the basis of regulatory criticality, latency, customisation needs, and total cost of ownership over five years.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Layer", "Choice", "Reason"], ["LMS / core ledger", "Mambu cloud", "Same as Wio Bank; cloud-native; open APIs; faster than building"], ["LOS / workflow", "In-house, Temporal", "Workflow logic is competitive moat; needs deep custom"], ["Decisioning engine", "In-house, Python + XGBoost + Feast feature store", "Owns the core IP; risk team controls model"], ["Data warehouse", "Snowflake", "Standard; cheap at scale; native streams and tasks"], ["Pipelines", "Airflow + dbt", "Standard"], ["Document / OCR", "AWS Textract + Layoutlmv3 fine-tune", "Best-in-class for Arabic-English mixed VAT invoices"], ["Identity", "UAE Pass + Sumsub", "UAE Pass is mandatory; Sumsub adds liveness and global watchlists"], ["Open Finance", "Lean Technologies", "First IPA holder in UAE; broadest bank coverage"], ["Peppol ASP", "RTC Suite or Avalara", "FTA-accredited list as of accreditation deadline 31 July 2026"], ["AECB", "Etihad Bureau API", "Mandatory monopoly"], ["Notifications", "Twilio + OneSignal + Postmark", "Standard tooling"], ["Customer support", "Intercom + Cohere Command-R fine-tune for Arabic", "Arabic-first chat is a UX moat"], ["Anti-fraud", "Sumsub + in-house Benford / image forensics", "Layered defence"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.10 API Contracts", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-api-contracts", "text": "3.10 API Contracts"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Below are the seven core endpoints. They use REST over HTTPS. All requests carry a bearer token in the Authorization header. All responses are JSON. All amounts are integers in fils (AED * 100) to avoid floating-point errors.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.1 POST /v1/onboarding/start", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-1-post-v1-onboarding-start", "text": "3.10.1 POST /v1/onboarding/start"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Begins onboarding for a new SME (buyer or supplier).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"role\": \"buyer\" | \"supplier\" | \"both\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"tradeLicenseNumber\": \"DED-1234567\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"emirate\": \"DUBAI\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"trnNumber\": \"100123456700003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"uaePassToken\": \"eyJhbGciOi...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"consents\": [\"openFinance\", \"aecb\", \"fta\", \"peppol\"],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"primaryBankBic\": \"EBILAEAD\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 202 (Accepted):", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"applicationId\": \"app_01HZX...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"kybStatus\": \"in_progress\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"nextStep\": \"open_finance_consent\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"consentRedirectUrl\": \"https://lean...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200 (Final, when scoring complete):", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"applicationId\": \"app_01HZX...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"kybStatus\": \"complete\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"limitDecision\": {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"status\": \"approved\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"limitAmount\": 50000000,           // AED 500,000", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"currency\": \"AED\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"creditTier\": \"B\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"eligiblePlans\": [\"bnpl_30\", \"bnpl_60\", \"installment_3\"],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"expiryDate\": \"2027-05-08T00:00:00Z\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.2 POST /v1/invoice/finance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-2-post-v1-invoice-finance", "text": "3.10.2 POST /v1/invoice/finance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Supplier requests financing on a specific invoice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"peppolMessageId\": \"P-AE-2026-...-INV-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierTRN\": \"100123456700003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerTRN\": \"100987654300003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoiceAmount\": 25000000,            // AED 250,000", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"currency\": \"AED\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoiceDate\": \"2026-08-01T00:00:00Z\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"dueDate\": \"2026-10-30T00:00:00Z\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"financingMode\": \"recourse\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"requestedAdvanceRate\": 0.92,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"productVariant\": \"conventional\" | \"sharia_tawarruq\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"financingId\": \"fin_01HZY...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"discountRatePer30Days\": 0.0180,      // 1.80%", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"totalDiscount\": 540000,              // AED 5,400 (90 days)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"advanceAmount\": 23000000,            // AED 230,000", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"netToSupplier\": 22460000,            // advance minus discount", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"expectedPayoutTimestamp\": \"2026-08-01T14:00:00Z\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"assignmentNoticeUrl\": \"https://...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"shariaCertificateUrl\": null", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.3 POST /v1/buyer/repayment-plan", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-3-post-v1-buyer-repayment-plan", "text": "3.10.3 POST /v1/buyer/repayment-plan"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Buyer chooses a repayment plan for an invoice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoiceId\": \"inv_01HZY...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerTRN\": \"100987654300003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"plan\": {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"type\": \"installment\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"installments\": 4,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"frequency\": \"monthly\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"firstDueDate\": \"2026-09-01\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  },", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"paymentMethod\": {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"type\": \"open_finance_dd\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"accountId\": \"lean_acc_...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"scheduleId\": \"sch_01HZZ...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"installments\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"due\":\"2026-09-01\",\"principal\":6250000,\"fee\":75000,\"total\":6325000},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"due\":\"2026-10-01\",\"principal\":6250000,\"fee\":75000,\"total\":6325000},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"due\":\"2026-11-01\",\"principal\":6250000,\"fee\":75000,\"total\":6325000},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"due\":\"2026-12-01\",\"principal\":6250000,\"fee\":75000,\"total\":6325000}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"totalCost\": 300000,                 // AED 3,000 across the 4 months", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"effectiveAPR\": 0.18,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"directDebitMandateId\": \"dd_01HZZ...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"shariaTawarruqRef\": null", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.4 GET /v1/invoice/{invoiceId}/status", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-4-get-v1-invoice-invoiceid-status", "text": "3.10.4 GET /v1/invoice/{invoiceId}/status"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoiceId\": \"inv_01HZY...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"status\": \"financed\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierPayoutDate\": \"2026-08-01T14:00:00Z\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierAdvancePaid\": 22460000,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerPaymentSchedule\": [...],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"balanceOutstanding\": 18750000,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"daysPastDue\": 0,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"watchlistFlags\": []", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.5 POST /v1/webhook/peppol/inbound", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-5-post-v1-webhook-peppol-inbound", "text": "3.10.5 POST /v1/webhook/peppol/inbound"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Inbound webhook from the ASP. Idempotent. Signed with HMAC-SHA256.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Headers: X-Peppol-Signature: t=...,v1=...", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"documentType\": \"invoice\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"peppolMessageId\": \"P-AE-2026-...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierTRN\": \"...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerTRN\": \"...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"ublXMLBase64\": \"PFViaWxJbn...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200: { \"received\": true }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.6 POST /v1/openfinance/consent", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-6-post-v1-openfinance-consent", "text": "3.10.6 POST /v1/openfinance/consent"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Wraps Lean's account-information consent flow with our session and risk metadata.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.10.7 POST /v1/collections/restructure", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-10-7-post-v1-collections-restructure", "text": "3.10.7 POST /v1/collections/restructure"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Triggered by ops or by buyer self-service. Recalculates schedule, applies penalty, signs new instalment plan via UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.11 Sharia Variant", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-11-sharia-variant", "text": "3.11 Sharia Variant"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The conventional product offers fees. The Sharia product offers profit on a Tawarruq sale.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "BNPL plans: platform buys an LME aluminium parcel via a CMA-licensed broker on behalf of the buyer; sells it to the buyer on a deferred-payment basis at cost-plus profit; buyer authorises the immediate sale of the parcel to a third buyer to settle the invoice supplier; pays the platform on the agreed schedule. The whole flow happens inside the app in 30 seconds and is shown to the buyer as a single instruction.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Installment plans: identical Tawarruq with the deferred-payment schedule split into 2 to 6 instalments at a fixed profit rate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Invoice purchase from supplier: Wakalah-based agency. Platform acts as agent buying the receivable from the supplier; receivable is held in a Sharia-compliant SPV; investors share the actual return.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Late payment: no compounding profit. A flat administrative fee is charged. Excess collected is donated to a registered charity through the Shariah Supervisory Board.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Shariah Supervisory Board: Dar Al Sharia (preferred) or Shariyah Review Bureau. Quarterly fatwa renewal and annual audit.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.12 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 1", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-12-three-year-unit-economics-product-1", "text": "3.12 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 1"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Active suppliers", "500", "5,000", "12,000"], ["Active buyers", "1,000", "6,500", "15,000"], ["Avg invoices financed per supplier per month", "1.5", "2.5", "3.5"], ["Avg invoice ticket (AED)", "180,000", "200,000", "210,000"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "200", "1,200", "3,500"], ["Avg outstanding book (AED M)", "80", "480", "1,400"], ["Gross yield on book", "22.0%", "20.0%", "18.0%"], ["Cost of funds", "9.0%", "8.5%", "8.0%"], ["Net interest / fee margin", "13.0%", "11.5%", "10.0%"], ["Provision for credit loss", "2.5%", "2.5%", "2.5%"], ["Risk-adjusted margin", "10.5%", "9.0%", "7.5%"], ["Operating expense (% of book)", "6.0%", "4.0%", "3.0%"], ["Net contribution (% of book)", "4.5%", "5.0%", "4.5%"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "3.6", "24.0", "63.0"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Year 3 includes a small share (10 percent) of book in non-recourse mode at higher pricing. Sharia variant is assumed at 25 percent of book by Year 3.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "Product 1, Path 2: Buyer-Led Invoice Extension Loan", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "product-1-path-2-buyer-led-invoice-extension-loan", "text": "Product 1, Path 2: Buyer-Led Invoice Extension Loan"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Section 3.1 to 3.12 above sets out Path 1: the supplier-led model where the supplier sells the invoice, gets paid Day 1, and the buyer settles us per their chosen schedule. Path 2 is the mirror image: the supplier is paid in full on the original due date with no enrolment needed; the buyer separately takes a loan from us to make that payment and to spread their own outflow.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "These are two distinct products that share data, infrastructure, and customer base. Path 1 acquires through suppliers; Path 2 acquires through buyers. Both increase the platform's addressable share of UAE B2B invoice flow. The unit economics, customer journeys, and risk models are different enough that each carries a standalone treatment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.13 Path 2 Thesis", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-13-path-2-thesis", "text": "3.13 Path 2 Thesis"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Why a Second Product Inside Product 1", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "why-a-second-product-inside-product-1", "text": "Why a Second Product Inside Product 1"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Three reasons it earns its place as a parallel product.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Acquisition is not gated by supplier enrolment. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Path 1 scales at the rate suppliers join the platform. Path 2 scales at the rate buyers see invoices, which is daily across the UAE economy. A buyer can use Path 2 to pay any supplier with a UAE TRN, on any invoice, without the supplier ever knowing the platform exists.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Cleaner credit construct. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Path 1 has two counterparties, two underwriting weights, two pricing components. Path 2 is a single buyer credit. Underwriting is faster, pricing is simpler, and the regulatory treatment is a clean unsecured term loan.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Captures buyers who cannot get supplier-led terms. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Many UAE SME buyers face suppliers who insist on net-30 or shorter. The buyer wants 60 to 90 days. Path 2 gives them that without renegotiating with the supplier. Path 1 requires the supplier to enrol; Path 2 does not.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Globally Validated, UAE First-Mover", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "globally-validated-uae-first-mover", "text": "Globally Validated, UAE First-Mover"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This construct is well-established outside the UAE. Two (Norway and UK), Mondu (Germany), Hokodo (UK), Slope (US), and Resolve (US) all run buyer-led B2B BNPL as a primary product, collectively disbursing several billion USD per year. None operate in the UAE today.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Comfi is supplier-side. Tabby Business is retail-merchant focused. Pemo, Qashio, and Alaan are corporate-card spend platforms with statement-period limits. Beehive, Funding Souq, eFunder, Aura, and Zelo are all supplier-side invoice discounters. No UAE platform runs Path 2 at scale today. The first-mover holds the category.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.14 Path 2 Target Segments", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-14-path-2-target-segments", "text": "3.14 Path 2 Target Segments"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The customer is the buyer. The supplier is incidental, not enrolled.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Mid-market SMEs with monthly purchase volume AED 200K to AED 10M paying multiple suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Family-owned trading and contracting groups with several buyer entities under one ownership.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Service businesses (IT, marketing, HR consultancies) buying from product suppliers and freelancers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Hospitality, F&B chains and franchises with rolling supplier obligations.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Healthcare groups and clinics buying medical consumables and IT services (overlap with Product 2 customers; cross-sell trigger).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Construction main contractors paying sub-contractors and material suppliers under tight project timelines.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Annual buyer turnover AED 5M to AED 250M. Operating account at any UAE bank reachable through Lean Open Finance. AECB Commercial Score 600 plus for unsecured pricing; 550 to 599 with collateral or personal guarantee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.15 Path 2 Buyer Journey End-to-End", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-15-path-2-buyer-journey-end-to-end", "text": "3.15 Path 2 Buyer Journey End-to-End"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 1: Pre-Approved Limit", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-1-pre-approved-limit", "text": "Step 1: Pre-Approved Limit"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every onboarded platform buyer with operating account or Path 1 history is scored weekly for a Path 2 limit.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit ranges from AED 50K to AED 5M based on AECB, Open Finance flow, sector, business age, behavioural data.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit is shelved. Buyer does not need to use it today. It is available against any supplier invoice the buyer wants to extend.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit auto-refreshes monthly. Increases up to 25 percent per cycle for clean-record customers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 2: Invoice Capture", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-2-invoice-capture", "text": "Step 2: Invoice Capture"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Buyer receives a supplier invoice (any source, any format).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Three capture options: auto-pull from Peppol if buyer is on the platform's e-invoicing relay; photo upload via app; email forward to a dedicated platform inbox.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System OCR-extracts invoice details. Buyer reviews and confirms in one tap.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Verification runs in the background (see Section 3.17).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 3: Choose Extension", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-3-choose-extension", "text": "Step 3: Choose Extension"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "On the verified invoice, buyer sees four options:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Option", "Buyer Pays", "Cost (Conventional)", "Sharia Profit Rate"], ["Pay supplier on Day 30 from own account", "On Day 30, full amount", "0%", "0%"], ["Extend to 60 days", "Day 60, full + fee", "1.5% to 2.0%", "Same, deferred-sale Tawarruq"], ["Extend to 90 days", "Day 90, full + fee", "2.5% to 3.5%", "Same"], ["Split into 2, 3, 4, or 6 monthly instalments", "Equal monthly amounts", "1.5% to 2.0% per 30 days", "Same"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Pricing is risk-tiered. Tier A (AECB 720+, low DPD, strong cash flow) prices at the low end. Tier C (AECB 580 to 680) at the high end and may require collateral. Tier D referred or declined.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 4: Buyer Confirms", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-4-buyer-confirms", "text": "Step 4: Buyer Confirms"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Two-factor confirmation through UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Direct-debit mandate set on buyer's primary bank account through Open Finance Service Initiation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Loan agreement digitally signed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sharia variant: a Tawarruq commodity transaction screen records the LME commodity purchase and immediate sale instructions. Standard fatwa-approved language is auto-populated.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 5: Platform Pays Supplier", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-5-platform-pays-supplier", "text": "Step 5: Platform Pays Supplier"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "On the invoice's original due date, the platform initiates payment to the supplier's IBAN as listed on the invoice, in full, in AED.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Payment is made via UAEFTS for amounts above AED 1M, or via Instant Payment Platform (IPP) for smaller amounts. Same-day settlement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Platform debits the buyer's Path 2 limit by the invoice amount and activates the chosen repayment schedule.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The supplier sees a normal incoming payment. The remittance reference shows the buyer's company name. No platform branding is exposed to the supplier unless the buyer opts in.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 6: Buyer Repays", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-6-buyer-repays", "text": "Step 6: Buyer Repays"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Auto-debit on each due date per the chosen schedule.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Push notification 7, 3, and 1 day before each due date.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "One-tap reschedule, twice in any rolling 12-month period at 0.5 percent fee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Default escalation identical to Path 1, with one change (see Section 3.20).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.16 Path 2 Supplier Side: Minimal Touch", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-16-path-2-supplier-side-minimal-touch", "text": "3.16 Path 2 Supplier Side: Minimal Touch"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The supplier is not a customer. The supplier is a payment recipient. Three points of contact only.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Verification: when the buyer uploads or pulls in an invoice, the platform validates the supplier's TRN against the FTA register, the IBAN against the supplier's bank, and the amount against historical payments to that supplier (if any).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Payment: the supplier receives the full invoice amount on Day 30 (or whatever the original invoice date stated). They receive a remittance from the platform's IBAN with the buyer's name on the wire reference.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Optional notification: an email confirmation to the supplier with payment details. Off by default to preserve buyer privacy. Buyer can opt in to enable supplier notifications.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The supplier does not see, sign, or accept anything. They have no contract with the platform. They simply receive payment on time.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.17 Path 2 OCR and Invoice Verification", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-17-path-2-ocr-and-invoice-verification", "text": "3.17 Path 2 OCR and Invoice Verification"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Higher anti-fraud burden than Path 1 because the supplier is not enrolled and cannot validate the invoice. The platform stands alone in verifying that the invoice is real.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Verification Stack", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "verification-stack", "text": "Verification Stack"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "FTA TRN check: supplier's TRN matches a registered UAE entity in the FTA register.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Bank account check: supplier IBAN belongs to the same legal entity as the TRN. Verified via the bank's account-name lookup API where available, or via a small penny-drop on first payment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Duplicate-pledge check: same invoice number plus same supplier TRN not previously financed on the platform, by this buyer or any other.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Buyer-supplier history: pattern check against the buyer's historical payments to this supplier (Open Finance bank statement scan).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Phantom-supplier check: new suppliers receiving above AED 250K go through enhanced review. Platform may call the supplier to confirm.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Round-trip check: the supplier IBAN does not belong to a related party of the buyer (UBO overlap detection on the FTA and MOET registers).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Image forensics: tampering detection, font substitution, screenshot edits.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Peppol-validated invoices skip most checks (FTA already attested the document).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Limits and Cooldowns", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "limits-and-cooldowns", "text": "Limits and Cooldowns"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "First payment to a new supplier is capped at AED 100K regardless of buyer limit.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cooldown period of 14 days before a new supplier can receive a second payment from the same buyer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Aggregate Path 2 exposure to a single supplier (across all buyers) capped at 1 percent of book.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Same-day same-buyer disbursement cap: AED 500K total to all suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Above any cap requires manual review with up to 4-hour SLA.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.18 Path 2 Risk Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-18-path-2-risk-model", "text": "3.18 Path 2 Risk Model"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Pure buyer credit. Supplier risk reduced to fraud and verification only.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Buyer Credit Inputs", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "buyer-credit-inputs", "text": "Buyer Credit Inputs"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "AECB Commercial Score (300 to 900) is the primary input.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Open Finance flow signal: monthly inflow and outflow, balance volatility, expense patterns, returned-cheque history.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "E-invoicing flow signal where buyer is Peppol-active: outbound and inbound invoice volume, supplier diversity, anchor-customer presence.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Path 1 history (where buyer is also a Path 1 customer): repayment behaviour, dispute rate, cure rate. The single best feature in the model after AECB.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sector multiplier and business age.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "WPS-linked employer signal: payroll consistency, workforce stability.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Behavioural signals: app engagement, document submission speed, payment timing relative to due.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Concentration Limits", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "concentration-limits-2", "text": "Concentration Limits"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum AED 5M Path 2 limit per single buyer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 5 percent of book to any single buyer (cross-product, including Path 1 exposure).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 10 percent of book to any single sector.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 1 percent of book to any single supplier (across all buyers).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Maximum 25 percent of book to first-time buyer-supplier pairs.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Loss Expectations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "loss-expectations", "text": "Loss Expectations"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Lifetime expected loss: 2.0 to 3.0% of disbursement, depending on credit grade mix.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Annualised PCL on book: 7 to 10% (higher than Path 1 due to shorter tenor and fully unsecured construct).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Stress scenario at 2x expected loss is manageable within the platform's capital buffer and FLDG-style retention against the senior warehouse.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.19 Path 2 Servicing Operations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-19-path-2-servicing-operations", "text": "3.19 Path 2 Servicing Operations"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Same auto-reconciliation engine as Path 1. One operational variation: the platform initiates the disbursement to the supplier on the buyer's behalf and then tracks the buyer's repayment as a clean term loan, instead of waiting for the buyer to pay against an invoice the platform already paid the supplier on.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Disbursement reconciliation: supplier receipt confirmation logged against the buyer's loan within 30 minutes of UAEFTS or IPP settlement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Repayment reconciliation: buyer's auto-debit matched against the loan schedule. 15-minute polling on Open Finance.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Statement: monthly buyer statement showing all Path 2 loans, balances, due dates, available limit.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Customer support: 24/7 Arabic and English chat, same SLAs as Path 1.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cross-product view: buyer dashboard shows Path 1 and Path 2 obligations together. One source of truth on outstanding.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.20 Path 2 Collections Playbook", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-20-path-2-collections-playbook", "text": "3.20 Path 2 Collections Playbook"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Same five-stage playbook as Path 1, with two adjustments specific to Path 2.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Faster Day 1 escalation: because the supplier already has the money, there is no recourse path. Default goes straight to buyer collections; we do not wait for a supplier to refund or dispute.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Tighter restructure rules: limit one restructure per loan in a rolling 12-month period (Path 1 allows two). Multiple restructure requests trigger automatic limit review and possible reduction.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "All other stages (soft, tele-call, field/notice, legal, recovery) operate identically to Path 1.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.21 Path 2 Technology Stack", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-21-path-2-technology-stack", "text": "3.21 Path 2 Technology Stack"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Same core stack as Path 1. Differences are in the layers that touch the supplier.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Lighter supplier integration. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "No supplier portal, no supplier dashboard, no Peppol return-channel for the supplier. Just IBAN verification and payment-out rails.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Heavier OCR pipeline. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "More invoices land via photo upload than Peppol in the early years (since Path 2 buyers will pay non-Peppol suppliers). The Layoutlmv3 model and Textract pipeline carry more weight here than in Path 1.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Heavier buyer decisioning. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "No supplier offset to the credit profile. The buyer scoring engine is the only line of defence. Champion-challenger framework runs more aggressively on Path 2 cohorts. Quarterly model review instead of half-yearly.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Heavier fraud stack. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Phantom-supplier and round-trip checks are critical. Investment in graph analytics on the supplier-IBAN-UBO triangle is justified by the higher fraud surface.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.22 Path 2 API Contracts", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-path-2-api-contracts", "text": "3.22 Path 2 API Contracts"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.22.1 POST /v1/buyer/extension/quote", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-1-post-v1-buyer-extension-quote", "text": "3.22.1 POST /v1/buyer/extension/quote"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Buyer requests a quote on extending payment of a specific invoice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerId\": \"buy_01HZX...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoice\": {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"supplierTRN\": \"100123456700003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"supplierIBAN\": \"AE07033...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"invoiceNumber\": \"INV-2026-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"amountFils\": 25000000,             // AED 250,000", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"originalDueDate\": \"2026-09-30\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"sourceType\": \"peppol\" | \"photo\" | \"email\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"documentBase64\": \"...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  },", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"requestedTerms\": [\"60_days\", \"90_days\", \"installment_3\", \"installment_6\"]", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"quoteId\": \"qte_01HZY...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierVerification\": \"verified\" | \"pending\" | \"new_supplier\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"buyerLimitAvailable\": 230000000,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"options\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"term\":\"60_days\",\"feeFils\":437500,\"effectiveAPR\":0.180},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"term\":\"90_days\",\"feeFils\":750000,\"effectiveAPR\":0.220},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"term\":\"installment_3\",\"feeFils\":562500,\"effectiveAPR\":0.200,\"schedule\":[...]}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"validUntil\": \"2026-09-29T23:59:59Z\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.22.2 POST /v1/buyer/extension/confirm", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-2-post-v1-buyer-extension-confirm", "text": "3.22.2 POST /v1/buyer/extension/confirm"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Buyer confirms a specific quote and authorises the loan plus the supplier payment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"quoteId\": \"qte_01HZY...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"selectedTerm\": \"installment_3\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"directDebitMandateId\": \"dd_01HZZ...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"productVariant\": \"conventional\" | \"sharia_tawarruq\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"loanId\": \"lon_01J0A...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"disbursementSchedule\": {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    \"toSupplier\": {\"date\":\"2026-09-30\",\"amount\":25000000,\"rail\":\"UAEFTS\"}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  },", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"repaymentSchedule\": [...", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"due\":\"2026-10-30\",\"principal\":8333333,\"fee\":187500,\"total\":8520833},", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    ...", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"shariaCertificateUrl\": \"https://...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.22.3 POST /v1/buyer/extension/disburse", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-3-post-v1-buyer-extension-disburse", "text": "3.22.3 POST /v1/buyer/extension/disburse"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Triggered automatically by scheduler on the original invoice due date. Pays supplier in full via UAEFTS or IPP; debits buyer limit; activates repayment schedule.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.22.4 GET /v1/buyer/loans", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-4-get-v1-buyer-loans", "text": "3.22.4 GET /v1/buyer/loans"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Returns the buyer's full Path 2 portfolio. Active loans, balances, schedules, available limit, recent activity.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "3.22.5 POST /v1/buyer/extension/restructure", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-22-5-post-v1-buyer-extension-restructure", "text": "3.22.5 POST /v1/buyer/extension/restructure"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Buyer self-service or ops-initiated restructure. Recalculates schedule, applies penalty fee, signs new schedule via UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.23 Path 2 Sharia Variant", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-23-path-2-sharia-variant", "text": "3.23 Path 2 Sharia Variant"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Tawarruq remains the structure, with one mechanical difference from Path 1.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "In Path 1, the platform purchases an invoice from a supplier under Wakalah agency, then offers Tawarruq terms to the buyer. The supplier sells a real receivable to the platform.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "In Path 2, the platform does not buy any receivable. The platform does Tawarruq with the buyer only: the platform purchases an LME commodity, sells it to the buyer at cost-plus on deferred terms; the buyer authorises the immediate sale of the commodity through a different broker; the proceeds are used to pay the original supplier in full per the original invoice. The supplier receives a normal commercial payment in AED and is outside the Sharia chain. The buyer's deferred obligation sits with the platform on the agreed schedule.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Late payment: standard Sharia treatment. Flat administrative charge donated to charity through the Shariah Supervisory Board; no compounding profit. Acceleration clause for events of default.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This variant is simpler than Path 1's Sharia structure because there is only one party to the Sharia contract chain (the buyer). No Wakalah agency, no receivable assignment, no SPV holding the receivable.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "3.24 Path 2 Three-Year Unit Economics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "3-24-path-2-three-year-unit-economics", "text": "3.24 Path 2 Three-Year Unit Economics"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Smaller volumes than Path 1 in Year 1 to Year 2 because Path 2 needs a buyer base to scale, which Path 1 helps build. Path 2 then grows fast in Year 3 once the cross-sell from Path 1 customers and direct buyer acquisition compound.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Active buyers using Path 2", "300", "2,500", "8,000"], ["Avg invoices extended per buyer per month", "2", "3", "4"], ["Avg invoice amount extended (AED)", "150,000", "150,000", "180,000"], ["Avg tenor (days)", "75", "90", "100"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "100", "500", "1,500"], ["Avg outstanding book (AED M)", "27", "137", "411"], ["Gross yield on book", "28.0%", "26.0%", "25.0%"], ["Cost of funds", "9.0%", "8.5%", "8.0%"], ["Net interest / fee margin", "19.0%", "17.5%", "17.0%"], ["Provision for credit loss (annual on book)", "5.5%", "7.5%", "8.0%"], ["Risk-adjusted margin", "13.5%", "10.0%", "9.0%"], ["Operating expense (% of book)", "8.0%", "4.0%", "2.5%"], ["Net contribution (% of book)", "5.5%", "6.0%", "6.5%"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "1.5", "8.2", "26.7"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Year 1 is light because volumes ramp slowly while operating cost is front-loaded for the underwriting team build and OCR pipeline maturation. Year 2 inflects as the buyer base grows and the model improves on real cohort data. Year 3 is the meaningful contributor.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Sensitivity", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "sensitivity", "text": "Sensitivity"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Scenario", "Trigger", "Year 3 Net Contribution Impact"], ["Base", "PCL 8.0% on book; yield 25%", "AED 26.7M"], ["Stressed losses", "PCL to 11% on book", "Down AED 12M; Year 3 net AED 14.7M"], ["Tighter underwriting", "PCL to 6% on book", "Up AED 8M; Year 3 net AED 34.7M"], ["Higher yield", "Yield to 28% (subprime mix up)", "Up AED 12M; Year 3 net AED 38.7M"], ["Lower scale", "Buyer adoption 50% of plan", "Down AED 13M; Year 3 net AED 13.4M"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Path 2 is more sensitive to credit losses than Path 1. A 100 basis point increase in PCL on book reduces Year 3 net contribution by approximately AED 4 million. A tighter underwriting policy that shaves PCL by 100 bps adds the same back.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Combined Product 1 Economics: Path 1 plus Path 2", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "combined-product-1-economics-path-1-plus-path-2", "text": "Combined Product 1 Economics: Path 1 plus Path 2"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Combined Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "300", "1,700", "5,000"], ["Avg outstanding book (AED M)", "107", "617", "1,811"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "5.1", "32.2", "89.7"], ["Net contribution as % of book", "4.8%", "5.2%", "5.0%"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Path 2 contributes 30 percent of combined Product 1 net contribution on 30 percent of combined disbursement, at slightly higher yield and slightly tighter risk-adjusted margin per dirham of book. The two paths together make Product 1 a AED 5 billion disbursement engine by Year 3 with AED 90 million of net contribution.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "4. Product 2: Healthcare Insurance Receivables Engine", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-product-2-healthcare-insurance-receivables-engin", "text": "4. Product 2: Healthcare Insurance Receivables Engine"}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.1 Product Thesis", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-1-product-thesis", "text": "4.1 Product Thesis"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "UAE annual medical claim flow runs at AED 22 billion. At any moment, AED 5 to 6 billion is outstanding to providers waiting on insurer settlement. Cycles run 60 to 112 days even after the regulator's shift to electronic adjudication. This is a structural working capital pain for clinics, polyclinics, day-surgery centres, dental groups, pharmacy chains, diagnostic centres and homecare providers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Klaim has built the first specialist platform in this space and partners with EDB. We see four whitespaces left open.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Multi-payer aggregation. Klaim works one provider at a time. We design for whole-receivable-book purchase across all payers a provider deals with, in one contract.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Predictive adjudication. Most claims rejected today are rejected for code mismatches, prior authorisation gaps, or coverage disputes. A machine-learning model fed on historical adjudication outcomes can predict rejection probability per claim, letting us advance more confidently against high-confidence claims and discount more cautiously against low-confidence ones.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sharia ABS at fund scale. Channel Capital and Tharawat Tuwaiq have shown this can be done. We commit to a USD 100M plus Sharia ABS issuance via ADGM SPV in Year 2.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Embedded receivables finance inside HIS / EMR / PMS systems. Most providers run InstaHMS, Bayanaty, ClinicMaster, NextGen, eClaimLink, OpenEMR, Medware, ELXR. We integrate at the EMR / PMS layer so that a claim financed is one click from the practitioner who submitted it.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.2 Target Segments", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-2-target-segments", "text": "4.2 Target Segments"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Multi-branch polyclinics in Dubai (DHA-licensed) and Abu Dhabi (DOH-licensed) with annual claim volume AED 10M to AED 200M.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Day-surgery and ambulatory care centres.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Dental chains (5 to 50 chairs).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Diagnostic centres (radiology, pathology, imaging).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Pharmacy chains (10 plus stores) operating against insurer formularies.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Homecare and post-acute providers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Excluded from the initial book: standalone individual practitioners; hospitals (separate corporate-grade product); cosmetic-only clinics with high cash-pay mix.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.3 The Provider Journey", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-3-the-provider-journey", "text": "4.3 The Provider Journey"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 1: Onboarding", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-1-onboarding-3", "text": "Step 1: Onboarding"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider authenticates via UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls trade licence; DHA / DOH / MOHAP licence; Riayati registration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls AECB Commercial Score.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls historical Shafafiya / Riayati claim data via the e-Claim portal API where the provider has consented.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System pulls 12 months bank statements via Lean.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System asks the provider to plug in their HIS / PMS using one of our four pre-built connectors (Bayanaty, InstaHMS, ClinicMaster, eClaimLink). Other systems ride a generic CSV / FHIR adapter.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 2: Receivable Book Onboarding", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-2-receivable-book-onboarding", "text": "Step 2: Receivable Book Onboarding"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System ingests the provider's outstanding receivable book: insurer name, claim ID, date of service, claim amount, status (submitted, resubmitted, partial, approved, paid).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "System runs the Predictive Adjudication Model on each claim and outputs an expected-recovery score.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider sees a dashboard: total outstanding, expected recoverable, eligible for advance, advance rate per insurer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 3: Advance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-3-advance", "text": "Step 3: Advance"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider selects the claims to fund (default: all eligible). Advance rate ranges 70 to 90 percent depending on insurer credit, claim type, and predictive score.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Funds are wired within 24 hours. SLA backstop is 48 hours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Pricing is a discount on the face value of the claim, not an interest rate. Typical 1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days against an expected 60 to 90 day insurer pay-out.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 4: Collection from Insurer", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-4-collection-from-insurer", "text": "Step 4: Collection from Insurer"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "As provider, the platform stands in the position of receiver. Notice of assignment is filed with each insurer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Most insurers settle into a master collection account designated by the provider.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Reconciliation matches insurer remittance to specific claim IDs using insurer remittance advice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Where claims are partially settled or rejected, the system splits the cash, applies the assigned share to the platform, and books the rejection back to the provider per the master agreement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 5: Resubmission and Recovery", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-5-resubmission-and-recovery", "text": "Step 5: Resubmission and Recovery"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Rejected claims are routed to the provider's coding team with the rejection reason and a suggested fix from our Predictive Adjudication Model.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Resubmissions are tracked. Recovery rates feed back into the model for continuous learning.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Where the provider does not resubmit within 30 days, the platform's in-house claim-resolution team takes over for an additional fee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.4 The Insurer / Payer Side", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-4-the-insurer-payer-side", "text": "4.4 The Insurer / Payer Side"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "We do not contract with insurers as customers. We deal with them as counterparties. The set of payers we transact against is the standard UAE list.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Payer", "Type", "Notes"], ["Daman", "Government insurer (Abu Dhabi)", "Largest single payer; Thiqa, Enhanced, Basic"], ["Sukoon (formerly Oman Insurance)", "Private insurer", "Major commercial book"], ["Orient Insurance", "Private insurer", "Strong corporate book"], ["ADNIC", "Private insurer", "Mid-tier"], ["MetLife Gulf", "Private insurer", "Expat-heavy"], ["Cigna Insurance Middle East", "Private insurer", "International network"], ["AXA Gulf / GIG Gulf", "Private insurer", "Dental and outpatient strong"], ["Salama Islamic Arab Insurance", "Takaful", "Sharia-compliant book"], ["Aafiya / Watania Takaful", "Takaful", "Smaller; takaful"], ["Nextcare (TPA)", "TPA for many insurers", "Allianz Partners affiliate"], ["NAS Administration Services", "TPA", "ENBD subsidiary"], ["Mednet", "TPA", "Munich Re subsidiary"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "We rate each payer on credit, average days-to-pay, partial-payment rate, and rejection rate. Advance rates and discounts are tiered by payer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.5 Predictive Adjudication Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-5-predictive-adjudication-model", "text": "4.5 Predictive Adjudication Model"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This is the technical moat of Product 2.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Inputs: ICD-10 diagnosis code; CPT procedure code; payer; provider; date of service; place of service; patient demographics (age band, gender, nationality bucket); prior authorisation flag; coverage tier; claim amount; historical adjudication outcomes for the same provider-payer-CPT triplet.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output 1: probability of full approval.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output 2: probability of partial approval and expected partial percentage.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output 3: probability of rejection and top-three predicted rejection reasons.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output 4: expected days to settlement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Model: gradient-boosted trees stacked with a transformer-based text encoder for the free-text justification field.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Feedback loop: every actual adjudication outcome feeds back into the training set within 24 hours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Performance target: AUC 0.85 plus on full-approval prediction at the end of Year 1.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This model is also a product on its own. We license it to providers as a Coding Assistant SaaS subscription, charged per active practitioner per month, and as a free add-on to platform users above a usage threshold.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.6 OCR and Verification", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-6-ocr-and-verification", "text": "4.6 OCR and Verification"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Most providers send claims through Shafafiya (Dubai) and Riayati (Abu Dhabi) e-claim portals. The data is structured. OCR is rarely needed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Where claims are paper-based (older clinics, some pharmacy categories), AWS Textract plus a custom medical-form parser pulls fields. Layoutlmv3 fine-tuned on UAE claim forms handles a long tail.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Patient identity verification: Emirates ID number on the claim is checked against the patient registry through the provider's HIS, not separately.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Insurance card verification: each major payer publishes a member-eligibility API. We run a real-time eligibility check at the moment of claim purchase.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anti-fraud: flag claims with implausible code combinations (childbirth code on a male patient; major surgery without an anaesthesia code); flag providers with sudden 5x rise in claim volume; flag duplicate claim IDs across providers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.7 Risk Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-7-risk-model", "text": "4.7 Risk Model"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Counterparty (payer) credit. Daman, Orient, Sukoon, ADNIC carry investment-grade exposure. We size limits to each.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider credit. Even in non-recourse mode, dilution risk is real. Strong AECB score and clean cheque history are mandatory.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Adjudication risk. The Predictive Adjudication Model is the primary defence. Advance rates tighten as predictive score weakens.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Concentration. Maximum 20 percent of book to any single payer; maximum 10 percent to any single provider.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Operational risk. Resubmission and partial-payment handling are the most operationally intense work in this product. We staff it as a dedicated team from day one.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.8 Servicing and Collections", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-8-servicing-and-collections", "text": "4.8 Servicing and Collections"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Most servicing is automated. Collections is mostly insurer-driven, not provider-driven.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Insurer payment delay over 90 days: structured engagement at the insurer's claims-processing department. We carry direct relationships with claim heads at all major payers from day one.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Insurer rejection: routed back to provider per master agreement; recovery support for an additional fee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider dilution (refunds, claim cancellation): credit notes booked against the next advance batch.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Provider default: rare; managed via the standard Stage 1 to Stage 3 collections playbook used in Product 1.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.9 Technology Stack Specifics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-9-technology-stack-specifics", "text": "4.9 Technology Stack Specifics"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "HIS / PMS connectors: Bayanaty, InstaHMS, ClinicMaster, eClaimLink, OpenEMR pre-built. Generic FHIR / HL7 adapter for the long tail.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Shafafiya / Riayati API: managed integration with appropriate consent layer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Insurer eligibility APIs: integrated for the top 8 payers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Predictive Adjudication: Python service on AWS; gradient-boosted tree library (XGBoost / LightGBM) plus transformer encoder; FastAPI service.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sharia ABS: ADGM SPV with a Channel-style true-sale structure; trustee model with a Sharia-licensed trustee; investor onboarding via fund administrator.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.10 API Contracts", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-api-contracts", "text": "4.10 API Contracts"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "4.10.1 POST /v1/provider/onboard", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-1-post-v1-provider-onboard", "text": "4.10.1 POST /v1/provider/onboard"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"providerName\": \"Acme Polyclinic LLC\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"licence\": { \"authority\": \"DHA\", \"number\": \"...\" },", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"riayatiId\": \"...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"hisConnector\": \"bayanaty\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"hisCredentials\": { ... }   // OAuth token, encrypted at rest", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "4.10.2 POST /v1/claims/import", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-2-post-v1-claims-import", "text": "4.10.2 POST /v1/claims/import"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Provider's HIS pushes a batch of claims for purchase consideration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"providerId\": \"prv_...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"claims\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"claimId\": \"CLM-2026-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"payer\": \"DAMAN\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"memberId\": \"...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"emiratesIdLast4\": \"1234\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"dateOfService\": \"2026-08-01\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"diagnoses\": [\"E11.9\", \"I10\"],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"procedures\": [{\"cpt\": \"99213\", \"qty\": 1}],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"amountFils\": 35000,           // AED 350", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"priorAuthRef\": null", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ]", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "4.10.3 POST /v1/claims/score", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-3-post-v1-claims-score", "text": "4.10.3 POST /v1/claims/score"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Returns the predictive adjudication score for a batch.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"results\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"claimId\": \"CLM-2026-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"pFullApproval\": 0.82,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"pPartialApproval\": 0.15,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"expectedPartialPercent\": 0.85,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"pRejection\": 0.03,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"topRejectionReasons\": [\"Missing prior auth\", \"Code mismatch\"],", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"expectedDaysToPay\": 75,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"recommendedAdvanceRate\": 0.85,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"recommendedDiscountPer30d\": 0.018", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ]", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "4.10.4 POST /v1/claims/purchase", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-4-post-v1-claims-purchase", "text": "4.10.4 POST /v1/claims/purchase"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Purchases a batch of claims at the offered terms.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request: { \"claimIds\": [\"...\", \"...\"], \"acceptOffer\": true }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response: { \"purchaseId\": \"prc_...\", \"netAdvanceFils\": 4250000, \"payoutTimestamp\": \"...\" }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "4.10.5 POST /v1/insurer/remittance/inbound", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-10-5-post-v1-insurer-remittance-inbound", "text": "4.10.5 POST /v1/insurer/remittance/inbound"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Webhook for insurer remittance advice. Reconciles cash to claims.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.11 Sharia Variant", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-11-sharia-variant", "text": "4.11 Sharia Variant"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The Takaful book (Salama, Aafiya, Watania, the Takaful arms of major insurers) is purchased into a separate Sharia compartment of the SPV. The structure is a true sale of the receivable to a Sharia-compliant fund managed by a CMA / DFSA-licensed manager. Investors receive the actual collection less an agreed wakala fee. No fixed return is promised.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Conventional and Sharia compartments operate side by side. Providers can elect either. Most large polyclinics will run a mixed claim book; we accommodate both inside one master agreement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "4.12 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 2", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "4-12-three-year-unit-economics-product-2", "text": "4.12 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 2"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Active providers", "30", "180", "550"], ["Avg monthly claim volume per provider (AED M)", "0.6", "1.0", "1.5"], ["Annual claim flow on platform (AED M)", "216", "2,160", "9,900"], ["Advance rate (blended)", "82%", "85%", "87%"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "150", "800", "2,500"], ["Avg outstanding book (AED M)", "50", "270", "850"], ["Gross yield on book", "18.0%", "16.0%", "15.0%"], ["Cost of funds", "9.0%", "8.5%", "8.0%"], ["Net interest / fee margin", "9.0%", "7.5%", "7.0%"], ["Provision for credit loss (incl. dilution)", "1.5%", "1.5%", "1.5%"], ["Risk-adjusted margin", "7.5%", "6.0%", "5.5%"], ["Operating expense (% of book)", "5.0%", "3.5%", "2.5%"], ["Net contribution (% of book)", "2.5%", "2.5%", "3.0%"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "1.25", "6.75", "25.5"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Year 1 economics are weighed down by the Predictive Adjudication Model build cost (USD 1.5M run-rate) and HIS connector engineering. Year 2 onwards economics improve as the model matures and provider ARPU rises.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "5. Product 3: Anchor-Led Supply Chain Finance with Dynamic Discount", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-product-3-anchor-led-supply-chain-finance-with-d", "text": "5. Product 3: Anchor-Led Supply Chain Finance with Dynamic Discount"}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.1 Product Thesis", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-1-product-thesis", "text": "5.1 Product Thesis"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Reverse factoring against approved-payable invoices from large UAE anchors is one of the highest-quality SME credit assets available. The risk is anchor risk, not supplier risk. Yet UAE anchor SCF is concentrated in two banks (HSBC, Standard Chartered) at one end and a single emerging non-bank platform (Comera, partnered with ADNOC) at the other. There is no tier of mid-corporate anchor SCF programs at scale, and there is no UAE platform offering dynamic discounting where suppliers can self-select an earlier payment date.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "We partner with 6 to 8 anchors in Year 1 to Year 2: targeting one or more from each of: hydrocarbons / industrials (ADNOC group, Mubadala portfolio companies, IHC group); real estate (Aldar, Emaar, Majid Al Futtaim, DAMAC); ports and logistics (DP World, AD Ports); aviation (Emirates Group, Etihad Aviation); telecom (e&, du); utilities (DEWA, ADDC, AADC, FEWA); retail (Lulu, Spinneys, Apparel Group). Each anchor onboards their supplier panel.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The dynamic discount feature is the differentiator. Each weekday at noon, suppliers with approved invoices can review the standard payment date (typically anchor T plus 60 to 90 days) and submit a bid for an earlier date at a steeper discount. The platform clears the auction at noon plus 30 minutes. Suppliers who win get paid that afternoon at the bid rate. Suppliers who do not bid receive standard terms.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.2 Target Anchors", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-2-target-anchors", "text": "5.2 Target Anchors"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "First-wave anchors (years 1 to 2). Each anchor onboards 200 to 1,500 suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Anchor", "Sector", "Indicative SME Supplier Panel", "Indicative Annual Procurement Spend (AED B)"], ["Aldar Properties", "Real estate", "Contractors, MEP, FM, fit-out, landscaping", "8 to 12"], ["Majid Al Futtaim", "Retail / real estate", "F&B suppliers, contractors, marketing, IT", "10 to 15"], ["AD Ports", "Logistics / ports", "Logistics, equipment, services, IT", "5 to 8"], ["e&", "Telecom", "IT services, contractors, marketing, FM", "6 to 10"], ["Lulu Hypermarkets", "Retail", "FMCG suppliers, fresh produce, packaging", "8 to 12"], ["IHC Group portfolio", "Holding / industrials", "Trade, services, FMCG, healthcare", "7 to 10"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Each anchor signs a master Supply Chain Finance Agreement that covers: anchor identification of approved-payable invoices; commitment to pay the invoice on the agreed date directly to the platform's collection account; standard payment terms; arbitration clauses.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.3 The Anchor Onboarding Journey", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-3-the-anchor-onboarding-journey", "text": "5.3 The Anchor Onboarding Journey"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 1: Anchor pilot", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-1-anchor-pilot", "text": "Step 1: Anchor pilot"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sign letter of intent. Define pilot scope (one business unit, six months, AED 100 to 500 million annual procurement).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Integrate with anchor's ERP (SAP S4, Oracle ERP Cloud, MS Dynamics 365, Workday Financials). Approved-payable feed is the only mandatory integration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Onboard 50 to 200 suppliers in the pilot batch.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 2: Supplier onboarding (anchor-led)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-2-supplier-onboarding-anchor-led", "text": "Step 2: Supplier onboarding (anchor-led)"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor sends a co-branded letter to its supplier panel.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Suppliers visit a co-branded onboarding page. Authenticate via UAE Pass.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Standard KYB pulls (trade licence, AECB, FTA, Lean) but accelerated because anchor pre-validation is in the file.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier-pricing tier is set at onboarding based on anchor identity and supplier segment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 3: Daily Operations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-3-daily-operations", "text": "Step 3: Daily Operations"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor uploads / exports its approved-payable file each morning by 11 am.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Platform receives, reconciles, and shows the queue of approved invoices to each supplier in their dashboard.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Each invoice carries: invoice number, gross amount, anchor's standard payment date, discount-rate ladder for earlier payment dates.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier clicks \"Get paid early\" and either accepts the standard early-payment offer (a static rate, e.g. 1.5 percent for 30 days early) or submits a bid in the dynamic auction window (12:00 to 12:30 UAE time).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "At 12:30, platform clears the auction at the highest discount rate that exhausts the day's available capital.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Funds are wired to suppliers same-day.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Step 4: Anchor settlement", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "step-4-anchor-settlement", "text": "Step 4: Anchor settlement"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor pays each invoice in full on the original due date directly to the platform's collection account.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cash is matched against the financed invoice. Any spread between supplier discount and anchor payment is the platform's revenue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.4 Dynamic Discount Mechanism", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-4-dynamic-discount-mechanism", "text": "5.4 Dynamic Discount Mechanism"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The auction is the heart of the product. Mechanics:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Each invoice has a base rate (the standard early-payment offer, e.g. 1.5 percent per 30 days early).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Each invoice has a maximum bid (e.g. 4.0 percent per 30 days, the cap above which we will not pay the supplier early).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Suppliers submit a bid in basis points and a desired payment date.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "At auction close, we sort all bids by discount rate descending. We allocate available capital top-down until exhausted.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cleared rate equals the lowest accepted bid (uniform-price auction). All winners pay the same rate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Available capital is calibrated daily based on platform liquidity, anchor concentration, and risk appetite.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Suppliers who do not bid simply receive the standard early-payment offer or wait for anchor settlement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Why uniform-price auction over pay-as-bid: easier to communicate to suppliers; more honest bidding; market-clearing discovery price benefits both supplier and platform over time.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.5 Risk Model", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-5-risk-model", "text": "5.5 Risk Model"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor risk is the primary credit. Each anchor is rated separately. Investment-grade anchors get the largest panel limits; speculative-grade anchors get smaller pots and tighter rates.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier risk is reduced to fraud and compliance only. The anchor has already approved the invoice for payment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Concentration: maximum 25 percent of book to any single anchor; maximum 50 percent of book in any single sector.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor-payment delay risk: managed via direct engagement with the anchor's accounts payable team and via legal escalation provisions in the master SCF agreement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.6 OCR and Verification", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-6-ocr-and-verification", "text": "5.6 OCR and Verification"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "OCR is minimal in this product. Approved-payable feeds come from anchor ERPs as structured data. We validate against the anchor master file, the supplier master file, and the platform's duplicate-pledge database. Where any item carries an attached invoice PDF (rare in mature ERPs), we OCR it for audit trail only, not for decisioning.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.7 Technology Stack Specifics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-7-technology-stack-specifics", "text": "5.7 Technology Stack Specifics"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor ERP integration: SAP, Oracle, Dynamics, Workday connectors. Pre-built REST adapters with batch reconciliation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Auction engine: in-house, low-latency, deterministic. Daily auctions at noon UAE time. Order book visible to ops, not to suppliers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Liquidity manager: tracks available capital across anchor pots in real time.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor portal: light-touch dashboard for the anchor's treasury team showing committed payable obligations and any extra-term concessions.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Supplier portal: same as Product 1, with the auction widget added.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.8 API Contracts", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-8-api-contracts", "text": "5.8 API Contracts"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "5.8.1 POST /v1/anchor/payable/upload", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-8-1-post-v1-anchor-payable-upload", "text": "5.8.1 POST /v1/anchor/payable/upload"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Anchor or its ERP integrator pushes the day's approved-payable file.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"anchorId\": \"anc_aldar\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"asOfDate\": \"2026-08-01\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"items\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"invoiceNumber\": \"INV-2026-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"supplierTRN\": \"100123456700003\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"grossAmountFils\": 12500000,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"approvedDate\": \"2026-08-01\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"standardPayDate\": \"2026-10-30\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "      \"poReference\": \"PO-...\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    }", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ]", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "5.8.2 POST /v1/auction/bid", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-8-2-post-v1-auction-bid", "text": "5.8.2 POST /v1/auction/bid"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Request:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"invoiceNumber\": \"INV-2026-0001\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"supplierId\": \"sup_...\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"bidRateBps\": 220,                 // 2.20% per 30 days early", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"desiredPayDate\": \"2026-08-02\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"validUntil\": \"2026-08-01T12:30:00Z\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "5.8.3 GET /v1/auction/{date}/results", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-8-3-get-v1-auction-date-results", "text": "5.8.3 GET /v1/auction/{date}/results"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Response 200:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "{", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"clearingDate\": \"2026-08-01\",", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"clearingRateBps\": 195,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"totalCleared\": 73000000,", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  \"yourBids\": [", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "    {\"invoiceNumber\":\"...\",\"status\":\"won\",\"effectiveRateBps\":195}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "  ]", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "}", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "5.8.4 POST /v1/anchor/remittance/inbound", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-8-4-post-v1-anchor-remittance-inbound", "text": "5.8.4 POST /v1/anchor/remittance/inbound"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Anchor pays on the standard date. Webhook reconciles.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.9 Sharia Variant", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-9-sharia-variant", "text": "5.9 Sharia Variant"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Murabaha-based reverse factoring. The platform purchases the receivable from the supplier on a true-sale Murabaha basis at a discount. Anchor pays the platform on the original due date. No interest. The discount represents the platform's profit on the original purchase. Supplier signs a Murabaha sale agreement on first onboarding; subsequent transactions reference that master agreement. Auctions in the Sharia variant clear on the same uniform-price basis but with profit rate language replacing discount rate language.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "5.10 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 3", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "5-10-three-year-unit-economics-product-3", "text": "5.10 Three-Year Unit Economics: Product 3"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Live anchor partners", "3", "8", "15"], ["Avg suppliers per anchor", "100", "300", "500"], ["Total active suppliers", "300", "2,400", "7,500"], ["Avg ticket per financed invoice (AED)", "150,000", "180,000", "200,000"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "300", "1,500", "4,000"], ["Avg outstanding book (AED M)", "90", "450", "1,200"], ["Gross yield on book", "14.0%", "13.0%", "12.0%"], ["Cost of funds", "8.5%", "8.0%", "7.5%"], ["Net interest / fee margin", "5.5%", "5.0%", "4.5%"], ["Provision for credit loss", "0.5%", "0.5%", "0.5%"], ["Risk-adjusted margin", "5.0%", "4.5%", "4.0%"], ["Operating expense (% of book)", "3.0%", "2.0%", "1.5%"], ["Net contribution (% of book)", "2.0%", "2.5%", "2.5%"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "1.8", "11.25", "30.0"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Anchor SCF runs at thinner margins than Product 1 because the credit is much higher quality. Margins are recovered through volume and the auction premium captured from suppliers willing to bid for earlier dates.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "6. Cross-Product Engineering and Operations", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-cross-product-engineering-and-operations", "text": "6. Cross-Product Engineering and Operations"}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.1 Single SME Identity", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-1-single-sme-identity", "text": "6.1 Single SME Identity"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Across the three products, an SME may appear as a supplier in Product 1, a buyer in Product 1, a polyclinic in Product 2, and a supplier in Product 3. We assign one canonical SME identity at the platform level. Each product references this identity. KYB is done once. Limits are tracked at the canonical identity level. A buyer in Product 1 with AED 1M of outstanding BNPL is not separately reachable for AED 1M of supplier non-recourse financing in Product 1; their group exposure is netted.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.2 Capital Stack and Funding", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-2-capital-stack-and-funding", "text": "6.2 Capital Stack and Funding"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Layer", "Source", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3", "Cost (indicative)"], ["Senior warehouse (USD)", "Pollen Street / Channel Capital / Stride / EBRD", "USD 50M", "USD 150M", "USD 400M", "SOFR + 4.5% to 6%"], ["Senior warehouse (AED)", "FAB / ADCB / Mashreq", "AED 100M", "AED 400M", "AED 1B", "EIBOR + 3.5% to 4.5%"], ["Mezzanine", "Shorooq / Family offices / Channel mezz", "USD 10M", "USD 25M", "USD 60M", "SOFR + 8% to 10%"], ["Sharia ABS", "ADGM SPV; investors via fund admin", "0", "USD 25M", "USD 100M", "Profit rate 8% to 11%"], ["EDB credit guarantee", "Up to 50% on eligible facilities", "AED 50M", "AED 200M", "AED 500M", "Guarantee fee 0.5% to 1.0%"], ["Equity (Tier 1)", "Lead institutional + group capital", "USD 20M", "USD 30M", "USD 50M", "Cost of equity 18% to 22%"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.3 Risk Governance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-3-risk-governance", "text": "6.3 Risk Governance"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Three-line-of-defence model. Product and engineering at the first line. Risk and compliance at the second line. Internal audit at the third line.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Weekly Credit Forum chaired by the CRO. Reviews scorecard performance, watchlist, exception requests, anchor onboarding, sector limits.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Monthly Asset Liability Committee. Reviews funding mix, currency exposure, duration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Quarterly Sharia Supervisory Board meeting and annual audit. Findings published internally.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Annual board-level credit policy review.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.4 Build Sequence (24-Month Plan)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-4-build-sequence-24-month-plan", "text": "6.4 Build Sequence (24-Month Plan)"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Quarter", "Product 1", "Product 2", "Product 3", "Platform"], ["Q3 2026", "MVP supplier-side discounting; OCR Phase 1; basic decisioning", "Klaim-style provider receivables MVP with 2 payers", "Letter of intent with 2 anchors", "ADGM Cat 2/4 licence; Mambu live; Lean live; AECB live; UAE Pass live"], ["Q4 2026", "Buyer side BNPL 30/60/90; Open Finance DD live", "5 payers; HIS connector for Bayanaty live", "First anchor live (Aldar pilot)", "Decisioning engine v2; Sumsub live"], ["Q1 2027", "Installment plan launch; Sharia Tawarruq live", "Predictive Adjudication Model v1; 8 payers", "Auction engine MVP; second anchor", "Peppol ASP integration; e-invoice flow"], ["Q2 2027", "Confidential mode; supplier non-recourse", "Sharia ABS issuance USD 25M", "Third anchor; dynamic auction live", "Snowflake / dbt rebuild; Sharia variants live across the board"], ["Q3 2027", "Embedded Wafeq / Zoho integrations", "Coding Assistant SaaS launch", "Fourth + fifth anchor", "Open Finance Service Initiation full coverage"], ["Q4 2027", "Iterate on installment plan UX", "Multi-payer dashboards mature", "Sixth anchor; first auction with 1,000 plus suppliers", "ESG / climate-linked overlay"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.5 Talent and Headcount", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-5-talent-and-headcount", "text": "6.5 Talent and Headcount"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Function", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Product (PMs + designers)", "8", "14", "20"], ["Engineering", "20", "40", "65"], ["Data and ML", "5", "10", "16"], ["Risk and credit", "8", "16", "26"], ["Operations and servicing", "10", "30", "60"], ["Sales and partnerships", "8", "20", "35"], ["Compliance and legal", "5", "10", "15"], ["Finance and treasury", "5", "8", "12"], ["G&A", "6", "12", "20"], ["Total", "75", "160", "269"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Indicative all-in payroll cost: AED 75M Year 1, AED 175M Year 2, AED 320M Year 3. This is the dominant component of operating expense and is what drives the operating-expense ratio compression as the book scales.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "6.6 Critical Dependencies", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "6-6-critical-dependencies", "text": "6.6 Critical Dependencies"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Lean Technologies API uptime and bank coverage. If a major bank is not Lean-connected, our installment-plan direct-debit experience falls back to post-dated cheques, hurting both unit economics and CX.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Peppol ASP partner reliability. We integrate with two ASPs from day one to avoid single-point-of-failure.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "AECB scoring quality on thin-file SMEs. Where AECB scoring is uninformative, we lean on Open Finance bank data and platform behavioural data; both need a clean cohort to start with.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "EDB credit guarantee processing time. Today this is multi-week. We design product flows that do not block on EDB approval; we apply for the guarantee post-disbursement where the guarantee is applicable.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Anchor SCF master agreement legal lift. First anchor takes 4 to 6 months; we standardise the template after that.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Predictive Adjudication Model training data. We negotiate retrospective claim history with each large provider at onboarding; smaller providers ride the cohort model.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "7. Key Risks and Mitigants", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "7-key-risks-and-mitigants", "text": "7. Key Risks and Mitigants"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Risk", "Description", "Mitigant"], ["E-invoicing delay", "Federal mandate slips beyond July 2027 SME date. Phase 2 OCR continues longer than expected.", "OCR Phase 1 stack is production-grade from day one; we can run on it indefinitely."], ["Open Finance bank coverage gap", "One or more of ENBD / FAB / Mashreq / ADCB lags in API readiness.", "Lean and Tarabut both integrated; secondary post-dated cheque fallback in place."], ["Anchor concentration", "First major anchor accounts for 40+ percent of Product 3 book.", "Hard 25% concentration cap from day one; Year 1 plan includes 3 anchors live."], ["Insurer payment delay", "Daman or another major insurer shifts to 120+ day cycle.", "Insurer panel is diversified; insurer-specific advance rates flex; direct claim-head relationships at all major payers from day one."], ["Predictive model underperformance", "Predictive Adjudication Model AUC below 0.75 in production.", "Conservative advance rates until model proves; human review for any model-flagged claim above AED 50K; champion-challenger framework with monthly back-test."], ["Sharia structuring delay", "Shariah Supervisory Board takes longer than planned to approve Tawarruq mechanics.", "Board engaged at design stage; conventional product launches first; Sharia follows in Q1 2027."], ["Funding line covenant breach", "NPL or watchlist exceeds covenant thresholds.", "Conservative covenants negotiated; quarterly portfolio reviews; cure rights pre-agreed."], ["Buyer abuse of installment feature", "Buyers chain installments to permanently float vendor obligations.", "Limit is set at canonical identity; new BNPL utilisation tracked across all open invoices; rolling 12-month behaviour scoring."], ["Fraud (synthetic invoices)", "Fraud rings issue fake invoices through Peppol post-mandate.", "Duplicate-pledge database; behavioural anomaly detection; cross-platform fraud information sharing through industry forum."], ["Regulatory shift", "ADGM or CBUAE introduces new licence requirements mid-build.", "Maintain quarterly engagement with both regulators; build with regulatory headroom in licence applications."], ["Talent", "Senior credit and engineering talent in UAE is scarce and expensive.", "Build a remote-first engineering org with India / Eastern Europe hubs; UAE-based for credit, ops, sales, compliance."]]}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "8. Closing", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "8-closing", "text": "8. Closing"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "These three products are not picked because they are easy. They are picked because the moats they build (e-invoicing-anchored data, multi-payer healthcare claim purchase, anchor SCF panels) are the moats that compound. Once an anchor is on, suppliers come for free. Once a polyclinic is on, every claim goes through us. Once a buyer has chosen an instalment plan once, they keep coming back.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The UAE SME lending market today is a bank market underserved by banks. The structural fixes (e-invoicing, Open Finance, EDB guarantees, AECB enhancements) are arriving in 2026 to 2027. Whoever builds first on these rails owns the next decade.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Built end-to-end on the model in this document, the three products together carry a Year 3 operating book of AED 3.45 billion, a Year 3 net contribution of AED 110 to 120 million, and a Year 3 ROA of around 3.2 percent. The path requires USD 100 million plus of senior warehouse capital, USD 30 million of mezzanine, USD 50 to 80 million of equity, and 250 plus people on the team.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The next decisions to take are: (1) sign off on the three-product scope; (2) begin the ADGM Cat 2 / Cat 4 licence application; (3) close the first anchor letter of intent and the first three insurer master agreements in the same quarter; (4) hire the staff product engineer, the head of data and ML, and the head of credit risk; (5) negotiate with Pollen Street and Channel Capital on the senior warehouse term sheet.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Two appendices follow. Appendix A lists the wider catalogue of UAE SME lending products surfaced in the underlying market research, beyond the three picked here. Appendix B sets out how an agentic AI architecture lifts every part of the operation, from KYB to collections to risk monitoring.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "Appendix A: Wider Product Catalogue", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "appendix-a-wider-product-catalogue", "text": "Appendix A: Wider Product Catalogue"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The three products in the main body were picked for differentiation, AUM scale, and timing against the e-invoicing and Open Finance ramp. The wider catalogue below surfaces seventeen further opportunities. Several pair naturally with the three flagship products as cross-sell extensions; others stand alone.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Each item carries a one-line target, the structure, the indicative AUM at maturity, and the reason it is whitespace today. AUM figures are 3 to 5 year potential, not Year 1 targets.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "A.1 Catalogue Summary", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a-1-catalogue-summary", "text": "A.1 Catalogue Summary"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["#", "Product", "Category", "Indicative AUM at Maturity (AED M)"], ["A1", "DMCC Gold and Commodity Murabaha Trade Line", "Trade", "5,000"], ["A2", "EDB-Guaranteed Sharia Term Lending Co-Lend", "Working Capital", "3,000"], ["A3", "Insurance Premium Financing for SME Group Medical", "Hybrid", "1,500"], ["A4", "WPS-Linked SME Payroll Stretch", "Working Capital", "1,000"], ["A5", "UAE-Africa Re-Export Murabaha", "Trade", "2,000"], ["A6", "Tokenised SME Invoice Marketplace", "Invoice", "1,500"], ["A7", "Franchise and Acquisition Finance", "Working Capital", "1,000"], ["A8", "Government Receivables Discount Program", "Invoice", "2,000"], ["A9", "Subscription / SaaS RBF for B2B Tech", "Working Capital", "600"], ["A10", "Embedded Accounting-Platform Lending", "Working Capital", "1,500"], ["A11", "POS-Receivables Merchant Cash Advance", "Working Capital", "1,200"], ["A12", "Marketplace Seller Financing", "Working Capital", "800"], ["A13", "Trade Licence and Visa Renewal Finance", "Working Capital", "400"], ["A14", "Corporate Tax and VAT Instalment Financing", "Working Capital", "1,000"], ["A15", "ESG and Solar Equipment Finance", "Equipment", "2,000"], ["A16", "Education Sector Receivables Finance", "Invoice", "700"], ["A17", "EWA Plus SME Payroll Bridge (Sharia)", "Hybrid", "600"], ["", "Total catalogue potential (excl. the three flagship products)", "", "25,800"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "A.2 Product Cards", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a-2-product-cards", "text": "A.2 Product Cards"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A1. DMCC Gold and Commodity Murabaha Trade Line", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a1-dmcc-gold-and-commodity-murabaha-trade-line", "text": "A1. DMCC Gold and Commodity Murabaha Trade Line"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: DMCC gold, diamond and metals traders with annual turnover AED 10 to 100 million. Structure: revolving Murabaha against warehouse receipts in the DMCC vault with hedged price exposure, 60 to 180 day tenor, ticket AED 1 to 25 million, pricing 8 to 14 percent profit per annum. Whitespace because most NBFCs avoid this segment for AML perceived complexity; an ADGM private credit fund with a strong AML stack and DMCC partnership can build a defensible book.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A2. EDB-Guaranteed Sharia Term Lending Co-Lend", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a2-edb-guaranteed-sharia-term-lending-co-lend", "text": "A2. EDB-Guaranteed Sharia Term Lending Co-Lend"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: Sharia SMEs in EDB priority sectors (manufacturing, food security, healthtech, advanced tech, renewables) with turnover AED 5 to 100 million. Structure: 24 to 60 month Sharia term lending with EDB taking up to 50 percent guarantee on facilities up to AED 10 million per ticket. Pricing 7 to 12 percent profit rate. Whitespace because only conventional banks have signed EDB MoUs to date; a specialist Sharia private credit fund unlocks ADIB and Emirates Islamic referrals on top of direct origination.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A3. Insurance Premium Financing for SME Group Medical", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a3-insurance-premium-financing-for-sme-group-medic", "text": "A3. Insurance Premium Financing for SME Group Medical"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: SMEs with 10 to 500 staff buying group medical (mandated by DHA in Dubai and DOH in Abu Dhabi). Structure: finance the annual premium AED 50,000 to 1.5 million over 9 to 12 months at 9 to 13 percent per annum, deducted from broker commission and SME WPS account. Distribution via brokers (Nexus, Aafaq, Mawarid Finance, HMG, Al Futtaim Willis). Sharia variant is Murabaha sale of premium voucher. Whitespace is structural; only Sehteq has a partial offering today.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A4. WPS-Linked SME Payroll Stretch", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a4-wps-linked-sme-payroll-stretch", "text": "A4. WPS-Linked SME Payroll Stretch"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: SMEs with WPS payroll history of 12 plus months and monthly payroll AED 200,000 to 5 million. Structure: 30 to 60 day bridge of one month's payroll, repaid from the next month's payroll inflows, pricing 1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days. Use cases: Ramadan cash-flow gap, summer slowdown, project completion delay. Whitespace removes a recurring pain point with a small, repeatable product.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A5. UAE-Africa Re-Export Murabaha", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a5-uae-africa-re-export-murabaha", "text": "A5. UAE-Africa Re-Export Murabaha"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: JAFZA, KIZAD, DAFZA traders re-exporting FMCG, electronics, building materials to Nigeria, Kenya, Ghana, Egypt, Tanzania. Structure: Murabaha 90 to 180 days against shipping documents and either a buyer LC or trade-credit insurance from ECI or Atradius. Ticket AED 1 to 15 million. Whitespace because African corridor SMEs are underserved by banks following the 2017 to 2019 corridor losses; an ADGM fund paired with credit insurance can re-enter.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A6. Tokenised SME Invoice Marketplace", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a6-tokenised-sme-invoice-marketplace", "text": "A6. Tokenised SME Invoice Marketplace"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: mid-market suppliers wanting access to a diversified investor base on receivables of AED 250,000 to 10 million, 30 to 180 day tenor. Structure: tokenised receivable-backed notes issued from an ADGM SPV with VARA-licensed token infrastructure for retail and HNW investor distribution. Differentiates from Beehive and Funding Souq by offering secondary liquidity. Whitespace is the unlock of a new investor pool through tokenisation rails.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A7. Franchise and Acquisition Finance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a7-franchise-and-acquisition-finance", "text": "A7. Franchise and Acquisition Finance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: F&B and retail franchisees of established brands (Americana, MAF Carrefour, Apparel Group, Landmark) and small business buyouts. Structure: senior plus mezzanine cash-flow LBO, 36 to 84 months, AED 1 to 15 million, collateralised by franchise contract, brand goodwill, equipment. Pricing 10 to 14 percent per annum. Whitespace because no UAE specialist exists; banks treat this as bespoke corporate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A8. Government Receivables Discount Program", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a8-government-receivables-discount-program", "text": "A8. Government Receivables Discount Program"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: contracting and FM SMEs supplying DEWA, SEWA, AADC, ADDC, Etihad Rail, MoEI, MOH, MOHAP, federal authorities. Structure: 30 to 120 day non-recourse discount of certified bills, AED 500,000 to 10 million, pricing 1.0 to 1.5 percent per 30 days. Combine with EDB guarantee for sub-investment-grade contractors. Whitespace because government invoices are high-quality but slow (90 to 180 days); banks ration this exposure due to internal limits.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A9. Subscription / SaaS RBF for B2B Tech", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a9-subscription-saas-rbf-for-b2b-tech", "text": "A9. Subscription / SaaS RBF for B2B Tech"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: B2B SaaS companies with USD 0.5 to 10 million ARR. Structure: revenue-based financing up to 60 percent of ARR, repayment via direct-debit revenue share, 12 to 24 month terms, 8 to 15 percent revenue share rate. Whitespace because Flow48, erad and FlapKap focus on consumer e-commerce; B2B SaaS RBF specialist is absent.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A10. Embedded Accounting-Platform Lending", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a10-embedded-accounting-platform-lending", "text": "A10. Embedded Accounting-Platform Lending"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: accountant-served micro and small SMEs on Wafeq, Zoho Books, Xero, QuickBooks, Tally. Structure: pre-approved 12 month lines based on full ledger plus Open Finance bank data, AED 50,000 to 2 million, pricing 1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days. Whitespace because CredibleX has Wafeq and Zoho via partner network; standalone embedded SDK with white-label brand is open.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A11. POS-Receivables Merchant Cash Advance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a11-pos-receivables-merchant-cash-advance", "text": "A11. POS-Receivables Merchant Cash Advance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: F&B, retail, salons, clinics with monthly POS volume AED 500,000 to 15 million. Structure: 80 to 120 percent of monthly POS advance, daily settlement split, 6 to 12 month tenor, pricing 2 to 3 percent per 30 days equivalent. Plug into Network International, Magnati, Mashreq NeoPay, Stripe, Telr, Checkout.com daily-volume APIs. Whitespace because Wio plus Network covers a small slice of around 70,000 merchants; the rest are open.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A12. Marketplace Seller Financing", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a12-marketplace-seller-financing", "text": "A12. Marketplace Seller Financing"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: SME sellers on Amazon.ae, Noon, Talabat, Careem Eats with USD 200,000 to 10 million GMV. Structure: lend against rolling 90-day sales, AED 50,000 to 3 million, 30 to 180 day tenor, pricing 1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days. Whitespace because consumer BNPL (Tabby, Tamara) is saturated, but seller-side B2B financing is empty.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A13. Trade Licence and Visa Renewal Finance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a13-trade-licence-and-visa-renewal-finance", "text": "A13. Trade Licence and Visa Renewal Finance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: micro and small SMEs at the annual renewal cycle. Structure: micro-loans of AED 5,000 to 100,000 to cover trade licence renewal, establishment card, visa fees. Tenor 6 to 12 months, flat 1.5 percent per month pricing. Distribution via Mal-style neobank app and free zone partnerships. Whitespace because the product is structurally absent today; SMEs use credit cards or unauthorised exchange-house lending.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A14. Corporate Tax and VAT Instalment Financing", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a14-corporate-tax-and-vat-instalment-financing", "text": "A14. Corporate Tax and VAT Instalment Financing"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: first-time corporate tax payers with AED 5 to 100 million turnover. Structure: short-tenor 3 to 9 month working capital aligned to FTA tax filing dates, AED 50,000 to 2 million, pricing 1.0 to 1.8 percent per 30 days. Whitespace because the segment is 100 percent green-field, growing as 9 percent corporate tax compliance matures from 2025 onward.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A15. ESG and Solar Equipment Finance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a15-esg-and-solar-equipment-finance", "text": "A15. ESG and Solar Equipment Finance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: manufacturing, logistics, hospitality SMEs investing in rooftop solar, energy-efficient HVAC, EV fleet conversion. Structure: 60 to 120 month Ijara, AED 250,000 to 15 million, subsidised rate 6 to 9 percent per annum. Combines with EDB renewables priority sector and DEWA Shams Dubai program. Whitespace because UAE Net Zero 2050 and IHC ESG mandate create policy support, but no specialist SME ESG lender exists.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A16. Education Sector Receivables Finance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a16-education-sector-receivables-finance", "text": "A16. Education Sector Receivables Finance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: tier-2 KHDA and ADEK schools with parent-paid term fees needing bridge against late-paying parents; ed-tech vendors selling to schools. Structure: 60 to 180 day discount, AED 250,000 to 5 million, pricing 1.5 to 2.5 percent per 30 days. Whitespace because education sector receivables are unaddressed by both banks and existing fintechs.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "A17. EWA Plus SME Payroll Bridge (Sharia)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a17-ewa-plus-sme-payroll-bridge-sharia", "text": "A17. EWA Plus SME Payroll Bridge (Sharia)"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Target: SMEs with hourly or blue-collar workforces. Structure: combine FlexxPay-style EWA at the employee layer (Wakalah-based, AED 500 per employee) with a parallel SME 30-day payroll bridge for the employer (Murabaha-based, AED 100,000 to 2 million). Pricing flat AED 25 to 50 employee fee plus 1.5 percent per 30 days employer line. Whitespace because very few integrated employee-employer products exist in UAE.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "A.3 Cross-Product Themes", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "a-3-cross-product-themes", "text": "A.3 Cross-Product Themes"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Embedded products (A10, A11, A12, A13) account for around AED 4 billion AUM potential and are the single largest theme by number of opportunities.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sharia variants (A1, A2, A5, A15, A17) align with Mal-style neobank distribution and unlock retail and family office capital.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "E-invoicing-anchored opportunities (A6, A8, A16) come into their own from July 2027 once SME mandate goes live.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Open Finance-dependent opportunities (A4, A9, A10, A11, A14) require the Nebras hub and Lean coverage to be at full scale, expected through 2026.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "EDB-guarantee-eligible products (A2, A8) get a structural cost-of-risk advantage where the guarantee is co-applied.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Sequencing recommendation if the platform expands beyond the three flagship products: A8 (Government Receivables Discount) and A10 (Embedded Accounting-Platform Lending) in Year 2; A2 (EDB-Guaranteed Sharia Term Lending) and A14 (Corporate Tax Instalment) in Year 3; A1 (DMCC Gold) and A5 (Africa Re-Export) in Year 4 once the trade-finance operation is staffed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "Appendix B: AI Leverage and Agent Architecture", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "appendix-b-ai-leverage-and-agent-architecture", "text": "Appendix B: AI Leverage and Agent Architecture"}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.1 Why Agentic AI for This Operation", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-1-why-agentic-ai-for-this-operation", "text": "B.1 Why Agentic AI for This Operation"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "SME lending is a sequence of micro-decisions taken under deadline. Verify a trade licence. Pull a bank statement. Compute a debt service ratio. Check sanctions. Score a buyer. Match a remittance. Send a reminder. Negotiate a settlement. Each step has a known input, a known output, and clear escalation rules. Each step today is partly manual, partly rule-based, partly heuristic. Each step is a candidate for an AI agent.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Agents are not chatbots. They are bounded specialists with tools, memory, and a clear contract. A platform-grade agent system is not one big model talking to a customer; it is a directed graph of small specialised agents, each calling APIs, each writing to shared memory, each handing off when its job is done. The orchestrator routes work; the specialists do work; humans stay in the loop where money, law, or reputation are at stake.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The economic case is direct. Year 3 plan headcount sits at 269 staff. Half of that headcount is operations and servicing functions where the core work is structured: reading documents, matching cash, writing memos, calling customers. A serious agent stack reduces the operations and servicing headcount requirement by 35 to 50 percent at the same volume, saves the equivalent of AED 40 to 60 million of payroll annually by Year 3, and ships customer experiences that no banks-on-banks competitor can match (sub-second decisions, 24/7 Arabic-first support, instant claim adjudication scoring).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.2 Architecture: Orchestrator and Specialist Swarm", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-2-architecture-orchestrator-and-specialist-swarm", "text": "B.2 Architecture: Orchestrator and Specialist Swarm"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The architecture has four layers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Orchestrator. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "A workflow engine (Temporal or LangGraph on top of Temporal) that defines the flow of work through agents. Persistent, durable, retryable. The orchestrator is not an LLM; it is deterministic state machinery that calls LLM agents as steps.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Specialist agents. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Each agent is a small program (often a single LLM call with tools) that does one thing and does it well. KYB, document parsing, cash reconciliation, customer support tier 1, fraud triage, credit memo writing. Each carries its own system prompt, tool list, and evaluation suite.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Tool layer. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "APIs to UAE Pass, Lean, AECB, FTA, Peppol ASP, Sumsub, Refinitiv, internal LMS and warehouse. Tools are wrapped behind permissioned interfaces; each agent has only the tools it needs.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Memory and observability. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "A vector store for retrieval; a relational store for canonical entity records; a trace log for every agent action with input, output, and tool calls. Langfuse or Helicone for observability; in-house dashboards for risk and compliance review.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Models are routed by task. Reasoning-heavy work (credit memos, settlement negotiation, regulatory horizon scanning) sits on Claude Opus or Sonnet. Routine work (categorisation, summary, classification) sits on Haiku or smaller open-weight models served on AWS Bedrock or NodeShift. Arabic customer support sits on a fine-tuned model (Cohere Command-R or an in-house fine-tune of Llama or Qwen).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.3 Agent Inventory by Function", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-3-agent-inventory-by-function", "text": "B.3 Agent Inventory by Function"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The table below names every agent we plan to build, the function they sit in, the tools they hold, and the human-in-the-loop checkpoint.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["#", "Agent", "Function", "Key Tools", "HITL Trigger"], ["1", "KYB Orchestrator", "Onboarding", "UAE Pass, DET/DED/ADGM/DIFC, MOET UBO, AECB, Sumsub, Refinitiv", "Sanctions hit, UBO mismatch, watchlist match"], ["2", "Document Parser", "Onboarding, invoice", "AWS Textract, Layoutlmv3, Peppol parser", "Confidence under 92 percent"], ["3", "Bank Statement Analyst", "Underwriting", "Lean APIs, internal categorisation rules", "Categorisation confidence under 90 percent"], ["4", "Credit Memo Writer", "Underwriting", "Scorecard outputs, AECB, sector data, peer comparator", "Always: human credit officer signs"], ["5", "Invoice Verifier", "Origination", "Peppol XML parser, OCR fallback, duplicate-pledge DB, Benford check", "Two or more fraud signals"], ["6", "Predictive Adjudication Scorer", "Origination (Product 2)", "ML model, ICD/CPT codebook, payer history", "Score below threshold"], ["7", "Anchor SCF Onboarder", "Origination (Product 3)", "Master template generator, e-signature, ERP connector wizard", "Deviation from template"], ["8", "Reconciliation Agent", "Servicing", "Open Finance webhook, fuzzy matcher, LMS write API", "Match confidence under 85 percent"], ["9", "Customer Support Tier 1", "Servicing", "Knowledge base, FAQ, ticket creation, payment lookup", "Sentiment negative; topic outside policy; AED above 100K"], ["10", "Early Warning Agent", "Servicing", "Cash flow analyser, behavioural baseline, AECB delta", "Customer flagged for watch"], ["11", "Collections Conductor", "Collections", "SMS, email, push, in-app sender; templating; cadence engine", "Day 5 (handoff to human)"], ["12", "Settlement Negotiator", "Collections", "Concession matrix, restructure proposer, schedule recalculator", "Always: human approves new schedule"], ["13", "AML Transaction Monitor", "Risk and Compliance", "Typology rules, transaction graph, SAR draft writer", "Always: MLRO reviews SAR"], ["14", "Sanctions Screener", "Risk and Compliance", "Refinitiv, Dow Jones, OFAC, UAE list, UN list", "Any positive hit"], ["15", "Regulatory Horizon Scanner", "Risk and Compliance", "CBUAE, FTA, ADGM, DFSA RSS plus parser; impact memo writer", "Material rule change"], ["16", "Auction Coordinator", "Product 3 ops", "Bid validator, clearing-price calculator, notifier", "Anomalous bid pattern"], ["17", "Cohort Analyst", "Risk and Product Analytics", "Snowflake, dbt models, cohort vintage report writer", "Cohort breaches threshold"], ["18", "Pricing Optimizer", "Product Analytics", "A/B testing framework, sensitivity simulator", "Always: Pricing Committee approves change"], ["19", "Anomaly Detector", "Platform Ops", "Datadog, custom signal processors, incident creator", "Severity above S2"], ["20", "Knowledge Base Curator", "Platform", "Document ingest, embedding generator, retrieval evaluator", "Quality drop in retrieval evals"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.4 Five Highest-Value Agents in Detail", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-4-five-highest-value-agents-in-detail", "text": "B.4 Five Highest-Value Agents in Detail"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Agent 1: KYB Orchestrator", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "agent-1-kyb-orchestrator", "text": "Agent 1: KYB Orchestrator"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Onboarding today takes 24 to 72 hours when documents are messy. The KYB Orchestrator collapses this to under 5 minutes for clean files.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Input: trade licence number, TRN, UAE Pass token, consents.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sub-tasks orchestrated: trade licence pull from the right authority API; UBO pull from MOET; AECB Commercial Score pull; sanctions and PEP screen on every UBO and signatory; address verification; FATCA / CRS check where applicable; previous platform footprint check.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output: a canonical SME identity record with confidence score, list of any unresolved discrepancies, and an onboarding decision (approve, review, decline).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Failure modes the agent handles itself: licence number entered with typos; UBO data inconsistent across registries; multiple Emirates ID matches for a signatory.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human handoff: any sanctions hit, any UBO over 25 percent in a high-risk jurisdiction, any politically exposed person.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Evaluation: golden set of 500 known-good and known-bad onboardings; weekly precision and recall review on sanctions hits; quarterly red-team exercise.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Agent 4: Credit Memo Writer", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "agent-4-credit-memo-writer", "text": "Agent 4: Credit Memo Writer"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "For tickets above AED 1 million, regulators and senior credit officers expect a memo, not a number. The Credit Memo Writer composes a structured memo from quantitative scorecard outputs, the bank statement analyst's narrative, sector commentary, and a peer comparator that retrieves the closest 10 customers in the book by sector, ticket, and tenor.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Input: applicant identity, scorecard outputs, bank statement summary, AECB, sector and macro context.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output: a 2 to 3 page memo with executive summary, financial review, risk factors, mitigants, recommended terms, and a one-line decision.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Tone is set by sample memos written by the existing credit team. The agent is fine-tuned on those memos.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human handoff: every memo. The agent drafts; the credit officer signs. Time saved is around 40 to 60 minutes per memo. At 200 memos per month in Year 2, that is 130 hours per month of senior credit time freed up.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Agent 8: Reconciliation Agent", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "agent-8-reconciliation-agent", "text": "Agent 8: Reconciliation Agent"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Cash matching is the single largest source of operational pain in any lending platform. Buyer pays through their bank with a wrong reference. Buyer pays from a different bank account. Buyer pays a partial. Anchor pays a batch covering 47 invoices. The Reconciliation Agent matches inbound cash to invoice IDs using fuzzy matching on TRN, amount, and remittance reference.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Input: every credit detected by Open Finance polling on the platform's collection accounts.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output: matched invoice IDs and a confidence score. Above 85 percent, the agent posts the match autonomously. Below, it routes to ops with the top 3 candidate matches and its reasoning.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The agent learns from ops corrections. Within 6 months it is expected to clear over 90 percent of inbound cash autonomously, against a baseline of around 60 percent for rule-based matching.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Agent 9: Customer Support Tier 1", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "agent-9-customer-support-tier-1", "text": "Agent 9: Customer Support Tier 1"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Arabic-first chat is a UX moat in UAE SME finance. Most banks still default to English. A genuine Arabic chat that handles 70 to 80 percent of tier 1 queries autonomously is a customer acquisition lever, not a cost-saver.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Input: customer message, customer ID, recent platform activity.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output: a response in the customer's preferred language drawing from the knowledge base, recent statements, ticket creation if needed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Tools: knowledge base retrieval; payment lookup; statement retrieval; ticket creation; escalation to human.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human handoff: negative sentiment; explicit request to speak with a person; topic outside the agent's policy (legal, regulatory, complaint); any AED amount above 100,000.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Evaluation: weekly customer satisfaction review on transcripts; daily precision check on policy adherence; live monitoring on hallucination rate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Agent 12: Settlement Negotiator", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "agent-12-settlement-negotiator", "text": "Agent 12: Settlement Negotiator"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "On a Day 5 collections call, the conversation has a small set of viable outcomes: full repay today; structured catch-up over 30 days; roll into a new instalment plan; refer to a payment plan beyond policy. Today, human collections agents make these offers from memory, occasionally getting the maths wrong, occasionally going outside policy.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The Settlement Negotiator runs in the background of a human collections call. It listens (with consent) or reads the agent's notes; it proposes the next-best concession; it computes the new schedule in real time; it generates the settlement letter.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Input: customer ID, current arrears state, the human agent's running notes, the customer's stated capacity to pay.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Output: ranked concession options with computed schedules and customer-facing letter drafts.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Constraints: the agent cannot offer outside the concession matrix. It always cites the matrix entry it is using. Off-matrix concessions are flagged to a supervisor.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human handoff: every settlement is signed off by the human collections agent. The agent is decision support, not decision maker.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.5 Tooling and Infrastructure Stack", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-5-tooling-and-infrastructure-stack", "text": "B.5 Tooling and Infrastructure Stack"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Layer", "Choice", "Reason"], ["Orchestration", "Temporal plus LangGraph", "Temporal gives durability and retry; LangGraph gives agent-graph semantics on top"], ["Model gateway", "AWS Bedrock for Claude and Llama; direct Anthropic API as redundant rail", "Region availability in UAE; SLA; Anthropic direct gives latest features earliest"], ["Reasoning models", "Claude Sonnet 4.6 default; Claude Opus 4.7 for credit memos and complex regulatory work", "Best balance of quality and cost"], ["Routine models", "Claude Haiku 4.5; Llama 3.1 70B on Bedrock for cost-sensitive batch", "Cost-efficient for high-volume tasks"], ["Arabic support", "Cohere Command-R fine-tune; Qwen 2.5 fallback", "Strong Arabic capability"], ["Embeddings", "Voyage AI or Cohere Embed v3 multilingual", "Best Arabic-English retrieval"], ["Vector store", "Pinecone or pgvector on Postgres", "Standard"], ["Memory", "Postgres for canonical entities; Redis for session state", "Clean separation of durable and transient"], ["Observability", "Langfuse self-hosted; Datadog for infra", "Full trace visibility, regulator-friendly audit"], ["Evaluation", "Braintrust or in-house; golden sets per agent", "Continuous quality gating"], ["Guardrails", "PII redaction at ingress; Anthropic safety APIs; output validators per agent", "Layered safety"], ["Deployment", "Container per agent; Kubernetes on AWS Bahrain region; UAE region as soon as Bedrock supports it", "Data residency aligned with CBUAE expectations"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.6 Build Sequence", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-6-build-sequence", "text": "B.6 Build Sequence"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Twenty agents is a long list. Build sequence matters more than build coverage.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Quarter", "Agents to Ship", "Why"], ["Q3 2026 (launch)", "KYB Orchestrator; Document Parser; Sanctions Screener; Customer Support Tier 1", "Onboarding and front-line support are the visible UX; sanctions is a regulatory must"], ["Q4 2026", "Bank Statement Analyst; Reconciliation Agent; Anomaly Detector; Knowledge Base Curator", "Core operational lift on cash and data"], ["Q1 2027", "Credit Memo Writer; Invoice Verifier; Predictive Adjudication Scorer (Product 2); Collections Conductor", "Underwriting and collections automation as volumes climb past Year 1"], ["Q2 2027", "Settlement Negotiator; Early Warning Agent; AML Transaction Monitor; Auction Coordinator (Product 3)", "Risk-side intelligence and Product 3 specifics"], ["Q3 2027", "Anchor SCF Onboarder; Pricing Optimizer; Cohort Analyst", "Scaling-stage agents"], ["Q4 2027", "Regulatory Horizon Scanner; remaining specialists", "Compliance modernisation"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.7 Risks and Guardrails", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-7-risks-and-guardrails", "text": "B.7 Risks and Guardrails"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Hallucination on numbers. Mitigant: agents that handle numbers always quote the source field by ID; no agent invents an amount; output validators check that any number cited matches a tool call return.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Prompt injection. Mitigant: customer inputs are sandboxed; system prompts are never exposed; sensitive tools (payment initiation, limit changes) require explicit human confirmation regardless of agent recommendation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Data leakage. Mitigant: PII redaction at ingress; model providers are bound by Data Processing Agreements with UAE-compliant terms; no PII enters non-Anthropic third-party logging without explicit opt-in.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Regulatory acceptance. Mitigant: every agent action is logged with its input, output, and tool calls; logs are queryable by regulator on request; agent decisions on credit are always advisory to a human, never the final decision.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cost runaway. Mitigant: per-agent token budgets; daily cost dashboards; model routing by task; aggressive caching on repeated reads; batching for non-real-time work.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Concept drift. Mitigant: continuous evaluation against golden sets; weekly review of agent precision and recall; rolling deployment with shadow mode for any agent change.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Sharia compliance. Mitigant: Sharia-specific agents (Tawarruq instruction generator, Wakalah documentation generator) operate from a Shariah Supervisory Board-approved template library only; no free-form generation of Sharia language.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Customer trust. Mitigant: any customer interaction is disclosed as AI-assisted; opt-out to a human is always available within two clicks; logs are retained for customer access on request, in line with the CBUAE Customer Protection Regulation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "B.8 Indicative Cost and ROI", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "b-8-indicative-cost-and-roi", "text": "B.8 Indicative Cost and ROI"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Annual run-rate cost of the agent stack at Year 3 scale (3,500 onboardings per month, 25,000 invoices financed per month, 6,000 customer support conversations per month, 1,200 credit memos per month):", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Item", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["LLM API calls (Anthropic plus Bedrock)", "USD 250K", "USD 1.2M", "USD 3.5M"], ["Vector store and infra", "USD 50K", "USD 180K", "USD 450K"], ["Observability and evals", "USD 80K", "USD 250K", "USD 500K"], ["Agent engineering team (4 to 12 staff)", "USD 800K", "USD 1.8M", "USD 3.0M"], ["Total agent stack run-rate", "USD 1.18M", "USD 3.43M", "USD 7.45M"], ["Headcount avoided in operations and servicing", "10", "40", "90"], ["Headcount cost avoided (USD)", "USD 0.6M", "USD 2.8M", "USD 7.5M"], ["Net economic impact (USD)", "Negative 0.6M", "Negative 0.6M", "Break-even"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "On a pure payroll-substitution view the agent stack pays for itself by Year 3. The real economic case is upstream: faster onboarding lifts conversion; better reconciliation lifts cash velocity; better collections lifts recovery; Arabic-first support lifts NPS; Predictive Adjudication lifts net interest margin in Product 2 by 100 to 200 basis points. Aggregate value uplift attributable to the agent stack is likely AED 25 to 40 million by Year 3, on top of the payroll substitution.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "Appendix C: Product Operating Best Practices", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "appendix-c-product-operating-best-practices", "text": "Appendix C: Product Operating Best Practices"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This appendix sets out the operating best practices that sit underneath the three product builds. They are not product-specific. They are the rails on which any well-run SME lending operation runs. Each section is written so a Head of Product can hand it to an engineering or risk lead and they know what to build.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.1 The Six-Stage Customer Lifecycle", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-1-the-six-stage-customer-lifecycle", "text": "C.1 The Six-Stage Customer Lifecycle"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Every credit relationship moves through six stages. Each stage has owners, exit criteria, and the data that flows into the next stage. Designing the customer view by stage keeps everyone aligned on where a customer sits and what should happen next.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["1. Application", "2. Assessment", "3. Approval", "4. Disbursal", "5. Monitoring", "6. Collections"], ["Intent capture, consent, KYB and data pulls. Funnel tapers sharply here.", "AI scoring plus deterministic gates. Predictive cash-flow analysis. Auto-generated credit memo.", "Offer with risk-based price, dynamic limit, contract execution.", "Funds in account in under 30 seconds via instant rails.", "Real-time portfolio monitoring, EWS scoring, behavioural signals, dynamic limit moves.", "Soft, tele, field, legal, recovery. Prevention beats cure."]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The discipline this enforces:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every customer is identifiable by stage. Dashboards show stage-mix, not just totals.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every stage has its own SLAs, conversion targets, and escalation paths.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Monitoring (Stage 5) is not a reporting function. It is the single biggest source of value protection.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Collections (Stage 6) is the smallest stage by design. If it gets large, Stage 5 has failed.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.2 Risk-Based Dynamic Pricing", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-2-risk-based-dynamic-pricing", "text": "C.2 Risk-Based Dynamic Pricing"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Flat pricing is a lazy default. Risk-based dynamic pricing centres customer prices on a target portfolio NIM while letting individual prices float by risk, behaviour, and elasticity. Done well, the bottom 20 percent of customers by risk pay enough to fund competitive rates for the top 80 percent.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Two Pricing Principles, Both Enforced", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "two-pricing-principles-both-enforced", "text": "Two Pricing Principles, Both Enforced"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The statistical principle: every pricing deviation is centred on the portfolio NIM target. Some customers price below the NIM, some above. The book in aggregate hits the NIM number every quarter. No exceptions.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The strategic principle: the goal is stickiness. Each customer pays the price that keeps them on platform. A high-elasticity customer (price-sensitive, multiple options) pays slightly less than the model would otherwise charge; a low-elasticity customer (relationship-driven, integrated workflows) pays slightly more. Both stay.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Pricing Engine Flow", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "pricing-engine-flow", "text": "Pricing Engine Flow"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Risk Inputs", "Affluence Inputs", "Sensitivity Inputs"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Pricing Modules (real-time + batch)   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Pricing Engine: APR(i) = CoF + μ + Σβ(j)·x(i,j) + Σ G(f)[b(f)¹(i), b(f)²(i)]"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Floor / Cap Governance: APR = min(max(APR, APR_floor), APR_cap)   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Approved Offer", "Selected Loan Amount", "Selected Tenure"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Where:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "CoF      = cost of funds (real-time from treasury)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "μ        = portfolio base spread (tuned to hit P&L and RAROC targets)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "β(j)     = linear coefficients for continuous drivers (tenure, amount, AECB score)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "G(f)     = N x M grids for two-way feature interactions (e.g. risk × affluence)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "APR_floor = governance floor (regulatory plus relationship-based)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "APR_cap   = governance cap (consumer protection plus competitive)", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "How Each Driver Moves Price", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "how-each-driver-moves-price", "text": "How Each Driver Moves Price"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Direction", "Pricing Effect", "Source Layer"], ["Risk", "Higher", "Higher price", "On-us behavioural model + AECB + alternate data"], ["Affluence", "Higher", "Lower price", "Declared income + estimated income + spend tier"], ["Sensitivity", "Higher", "Lower price", "Offer sensitivity, journey sensitivity, process convenience"], ["Tenure", "Longer", "Lower price", "β layer (continuous)"], ["Amount", "Larger", "Lower price", "β layer (continuous)"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Pricing Modules in Production", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "pricing-modules-in-production", "text": "Pricing Modules in Production"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Module", "Inputs", "Outputs"], ["Affluence Model", "Declared income; estimated income from bank statements; spend tier 01 to 10", "Affluence band per customer"], ["Risk Model", "Behavioural risk (on-us); bureau (off-us); alternate data risk model", "PD bucket and confidence"], ["Sensitivity Model", "Offer sensitivity (loan amount, price elasticity); journey sensitivity; process convenience", "Elasticity score"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Risk-Tier Pricing Bands", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "risk-tier-pricing-bands", "text": "Risk-Tier Pricing Bands"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Tier", "PD Range", "Annual Profit Rate", "Notes"], ["Prime", "0 to 3%", "12 to 15% pa", "Competitive against incumbent banks; speed premium"], ["Standard", "3 to 8%", "16 to 22% pa", "Mainstream SME credit pricing"], ["Near-Prime", "8 to 15%", "23 to 28% pa", "Below fintech and informal credit pricing"], ["Elevated", "above 15%", "Decline or manual-only", "No automated path; credit committee for any approval"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Governance and Audit", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "governance-and-audit", "text": "Governance and Audit"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every pricing decision is logged with the model version, feature contributions, and the resulting APR.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Pricing Committee reviews any deviation greater than 200 basis points from the model recommendation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Champion-challenger framework runs continuous A/B tests on 5 percent of portfolio volume.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Quarterly back-test: realised NIM versus target NIM, by tier and segment.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "No pricing override below the floor or above the cap without CRO sign-off.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.3 Decision Engine Architecture", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-3-decision-engine-architecture", "text": "C.3 Decision Engine Architecture"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The decision engine is the heart of the lending platform. Build it in-house. It has to be configurable by the risk team without engineering lift, and it has to compose three layers cleanly: deterministic policy gates, AI scoring, and the offer engine.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Six Stages of the Credit Application Flow", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "six-stages-of-the-credit-application-flow", "text": "Six Stages of the Credit Application Flow"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Stage 1: Pre-qualification", "Stage 2: Application Initiation", "Stage 3: Automated Decisioning"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Stage 6: Facility Activation", "Stage 5: Offer Generation", "Stage 4: Human Review (if needed)"]]}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 1 — Pre-qualification (background, continuous)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Weekly eligibility scoring on every active operating account. Pre-qualified offers surfaced inside the app: \"You may be eligible for AED X.\" No bureau hard pull yet.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 2 — Application Initiation", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Customer taps to apply. Consents to bureau hard pull and Open Finance pull. AECB report and 24 months bank data ingest. Application form pre-fills from on-us data; customer verifies, does not re-enter.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 3 — Automated Decisioning (Express, under 4 hours)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Three layers run in sequence:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Layer", "Logic", "Failure Outcome"], ["Deterministic Policy Gates", "Sanctions; not bankrupt; cheque bounce check; business age >= 12 months; AECB >= 550 hard floor", "Auto-decline with specific reason"], ["AI Scoring", "PD model + cash flow classifier + revenue stability + bureau tradeline + sector multiplier + behavioural", "Below threshold: decline; in band: human review"], ["Offer Engine", "Limit (capped at 15% of revenue) + risk-based price + tenor + variant", "Surface offer; or escalate edge case"]]}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 4 — Human Review Queue", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Edge cases route here: AI confidence below threshold; ticket above Express ceiling; sector concentration breach; first-time pair above policy. Credit analyst reviews the AI-generated memo. Approves, modifies limit or price, or declines with documented reason. Target SLA: 4 business hours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 5 — Offer Generation and Acceptance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Customer receives offer with full transparent terms. 72-hour acceptance window. Digital acceptance is binding for Standard tier; physical or DocuSign for Enhanced.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h4", "spans": [{"t": "Stage 6 — Facility Activation", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Sharia: Commodity Murabaha master agreement executed once at activation; each draw references it. Conventional: credit facility agreement. Customer can draw immediately.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Three Product Variants by Touch and Limit", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "three-product-variants-by-touch-and-limit", "text": "Three Product Variants by Touch and Limit"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Variant", "Limit Range", "Touch", "SLA", "Inputs"], ["Express", "Up to AED 250K", "Fully automated", "Under 4 hours", "On-us 12 months data only"], ["Standard", "AED 250K to 750K", "Semi-automated", "24 to 72 hours", "+ VAT returns + bank statements (off-us)"], ["Enhanced", "AED 750K to 2M", "RM-led, hybrid", "3 to 5 days", "+ audited financials + RM call + sector model"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.4 AI Where It Matters, Rules Where It Must", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-4-ai-where-it-matters-rules-where-it-must", "text": "C.4 AI Where It Matters, Rules Where It Must"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "A clear taxonomy of where AI sits and where rules sit. AI is decision support, not authority. Anything that has to be defended to a regulator must be explainable. Anything that has to be defended to a customer must be in plain language.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Deterministic Rules versus AI", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "deterministic-rules-versus-ai", "text": "Deterministic Rules versus AI"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Type", "Use Cases"], ["Deterministic (binary, auditable)", "Sanctions and blacklist screening; minimum eligibility thresholds (business age, revenue floor, AECB floor); exposure and sector concentration caps; affordability hard caps (DSCR floors, 15 percent of revenue cap); KYC and AML checks"], ["AI-driven (predictive, pattern-based)", "Probability of default modelling; loss given default estimation; cash flow prediction and volatility analysis; early warning detection; dynamic limit management; document verification and fraud detection; alternative data scoring for thin-file SMEs"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Real-Time, Near-Real-Time, Asynchronous", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "real-time-near-real-time-asynchronous", "text": "Real-Time, Near-Real-Time, Asynchronous"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Latency Bucket", "Use Cases"], ["Real-time (sub-second)", "Fraud checks at origination; sanctions and PEP screening; drawdown approval against existing facility; repayment processing"], ["Near-real-time (under 4 hours)", "Express full application decisioning; dynamic limit booster requests"], ["Asynchronous (batch)", "Portfolio monitoring and EWS scoring (daily, weekly); credit limit reviews (quarterly); bureau data refresh (monthly); model retraining and champion-challenger evaluation (quarterly)"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Customer Explainability via SHAP", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "customer-explainability-via-shap", "text": "Customer Explainability via SHAP"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Every AI decision has a SHAP-value record. Top 3 to 5 features are translated into customer-facing reason codes via a mapping layer. Right to human review is mandatory and prominently visible. Decline messages are specific and actionable, not generic.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Sample decline message"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "\"At this time we are unable to approve a facility. The primary reasons are: your business has been operating for 9 months (we look for 12+); a dishonoured cheque of AED 18,000 is reported on your bureau in August 2025. We will re-evaluate automatically in 3 months. You can also request a human review now.\"", "b": false, "i": true}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Model Fail-Safe and Fallback", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "model-fail-safe-and-fallback", "text": "Model Fail-Safe and Fallback"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Component", "Failure Scenario", "Fallback"], ["Credit scoring model", "Model server down or low confidence", "Queue for next run (max 4 hr); rules-only simplified scoring path"], ["Bureau API", "AECB unavailable", "Retry 3x over 2 hr; escalate to manual review"], ["Open Finance data", "Bank not connected", "Fall back to uploaded bank statements"], ["Fraud detection", "Model unavailable", "Conservative rule-based limits + human review for any drawdown above AED 100K"], ["Commodity platform (Sharia)", "Exchange API down", "Pre-approved internal commodity inventory pool"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.5 Early Warning System", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-5-early-warning-system", "text": "C.5 Early Warning System"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The EWS converts five categories of leading signals into a single risk score, which routes the account into one of four action paths. The model runs weekly and alerts on signal change, not just absolute score.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Signal Sources", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "signal-sources", "text": "Signal Sources"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Financial", "Banking", "Operational", "Behavioural", "Macroeconomic"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Trigger Engine + Case Repository + Risk Intelligence   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["EWS Score (Critical / High / Medium / Low)"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Signals by Category", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "signals-by-category", "text": "Signals by Category"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Category", "Sample Signals"], ["Financial", "Declining cash flow; falling sales and profit; adverse audit reports; poor working capital position; inventory or receivables pile-up; low ICR or DSCR"], ["Banking", "Cheque bounces; central fraud database hits; defaulter list entries; payment stretch; rising debt"], ["Operational", "Loss of key customers; supplier disputes; labour unrest; project delays; regulatory violations; management disputes"], ["Behavioural", "Negative media; analyst downgrade; lawsuits filed against; frequent device or location change; communication blackout; pending court cases"], ["Macroeconomic", "Sectoral performance; unemployment rate; inflation forecast; banking NPAs; recession indicators; consumer or political sentiment"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Action Paths by EWS Score", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "action-paths-by-ews-score", "text": "Action Paths by EWS Score"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Critical", "High", "Medium", "Low"], ["Immediate freeze Intensive review Direct engagement Initiate recovery System flag", "Limit management Proactive intervention Restructuring Enhanced monitoring", "Automated monitoring Suspend pre-approvals Soft engagement Portfolio review", "Standard management Growth opportunity Customer loyalty Automated monitoring"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The discipline: Critical and High are loss-prevention motions. Low and Medium are revenue motions. Both matter equally. A Low-score customer who never gets a relevant offer is just as much of a missed outcome as a High-score customer who slips into default.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.6 AI-Driven Collections Architecture", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-6-ai-driven-collections-architecture", "text": "C.6 AI-Driven Collections Architecture"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Collections is most economical when the model decides three things together: which channel, what time, what message. Inputs flow from three feeds. The model produces a recommendation. The strategy builder converts it into a campaign. Outcomes feed back into the next cycle.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Architecture Flow", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "architecture-flow", "text": "Architecture Flow"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Behavioural", "Loan Info", "Profile"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Collection Model (Data Science layer)   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["AI Recommendation → Strategy Builder"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Collection Campaigns   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Channel: SMS / IVR / Auto-dialler / Email / In-app / Field", "Time slot: best contact window", "Message tone: empathetic / firm / final"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↺   Feedback Loop: action taken; customer response; resolution outcome   ↺", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Why Personalised Beats Linear Cadence", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "why-personalised-beats-linear-cadence", "text": "Why Personalised Beats Linear Cadence"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Traditional collections runs a fixed cadence: SMS Day 1, call Day 3, letter Day 7. The AI model individualises every step. A first-time delinquent with a clean history may need only one nudge by SMS at 11 am. A repeat delinquent with negative bureau may need an immediate field visit. The same playbook applied to both is wrong twice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Inputs Captured", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "inputs-captured", "text": "Inputs Captured"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Source", "Sample Features"], ["Behavioural", "App engagement; response time to messages; preferred contact hours; channel preference history; tone-response history"], ["Loan Info", "Days past due; outstanding balance; original facility size; product variant; collection stage; prior settlements"], ["Profile", "Sector; emirate; ownership concentration; employee count; bureau trend; on-us cash flow trend"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Operating Discipline", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "operating-discipline", "text": "Operating Discipline"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Concession matrix is fixed by Credit Committee. AI and human agents both work inside it.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Off-matrix concessions require supervisor approval; logged with reason and outcome.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Recovery is sold to a recovery partner only after Day 90 charge-off and ops sign-off.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every customer interaction is recorded and auditable per CBUAE Customer Protection rules.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "No third-party debt collection without proper CBUAE-compliant notice.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.7 Rejection Handling and Credit Builder", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-7-rejection-handling-and-credit-builder", "text": "C.7 Rejection Handling and Credit Builder"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Roughly 50 to 60 percent of applicants get declined in the first year of any new SME lender. Losing them all is a strategic mistake. They are pre-qualified leads who just need 6 to 18 months of light engagement before they become customers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "The Credit Builder Programme", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "the-credit-builder-programme", "text": "The Credit Builder Programme"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "A goal-based feature that sits inside the app for declined applicants. The customer never sees a dead-end; they see a path.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Decline Decision", "Specific Reason + Goal", "Weekly Progress Tracker", "Auto Re-Evaluation"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   On milestone-completion or 90-day mark, re-score automatically   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Eligibility Reached → Proactive Notification → Pre-Approved Offer"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Mechanics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "mechanics", "text": "Mechanics"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Each declined customer receives a clear, specific reason for decline (not a code). \"Your business is 9 months old; we require 12.\" \"There is a dishonoured cheque of AED 18K reported in August.\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Each customer receives a personalised improvement target: \"Maintain monthly inflows above AED 100K for 6 consecutive months.\" \"Resolve the overdue utility payment on your AECB report.\" \"Keep your operating account balance positive for 90 days.\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Progress is tracked weekly inside the app. Customer sees their own score moving, not the policy.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Auto re-evaluation triggers at 90 days and at any milestone-completion event.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Proactive notification fires when eligibility is reached. Pre-approved offer follows.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Light engagement throughout: monthly digest, financial-health tip, short articles. Keeps the customer warm.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "What to Avoid", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "what-to-avoid", "text": "What to Avoid"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Do not expose policy thresholds in detail. Customers should know what to control, not the exact numbers we use. The Credit Builder communicates direction, not policy specifics.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Do not gamify the policy. A leaderboard or badge system around credit eligibility creates the wrong incentives and may invite gaming.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Do not let the Credit Builder become a no-touch dead-end. Engagement (chat support, monthly digest, financial-health tip) keeps the customer warm.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Do not bury the right to human review. Show it on the decline screen with a single tap.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Why It Pays", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "why-it-pays", "text": "Why It Pays"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Acquisition cost on a customer already on the operating account is near zero. Re-acquired customers who graduate from Credit Builder convert at 3 to 5 times the rate of a cold lead. They also stick longer, since they have walked the path and trust the brand.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "In Year 2 and Year 3, expect 15 to 25 percent of new credit customers to come from the Credit Builder pool. This is a structural advantage over fintech competitors who have no operating account base and therefore no warm Credit Builder pool to graduate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Right to Human Review", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "right-to-human-review", "text": "Right to Human Review"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Independent of the Credit Builder, every declined customer has the right to escalate to human review within 30 days. This is a CBUAE Customer Protection expectation and a responsible lending principle. Make it visible; do not hide it in the T&Cs. Human-reviewed declines also feed into model retraining: every override is a labelled training example.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.8 Funnel Design Principles", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-8-funnel-design-principles", "text": "C.8 Funnel Design Principles"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The funnel must taper sharply at the beginning, not at the end. Asking a customer to fill 10 fields and upload 5 documents only to decline at the bureau check is a broken design that wastes their time and ours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Three Rules", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "three-rules", "text": "Three Rules"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Rule 1. Eliminate early. The first three questions in any application must be the ones with the highest knockout probability: trade licence number, business vintage, monthly revenue. If any fails, tell the customer immediately and offer Credit Builder.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Rule 2. Risk check at every step, not at the end. The decision is not one API call after data collection. It is a sequence of micro-decisions, each of which can knock the customer out, upgrade them, or refine pricing.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Rule 3. Pre-approved offers above cold leads. Most users should see an offer before they apply. Pre-approved offers convert at 3 to 5 times the rate of a cold form. Build the propensity model on the operating account base.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Drop-Off Recovery", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "drop-off-recovery", "text": "Drop-Off Recovery"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Anyone who reaches more than 70 percent of the application and abandons is a high-intent lead. Trigger an outreach within 24 hours. A short call from a human, not another email. Call-to-conversion on these is 2 to 3 times higher than fresh leads.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.9 Affordability and Concentration Guardrails", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-9-affordability-and-concentration-guardrails", "text": "C.9 Affordability and Concentration Guardrails"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Hard rules, enforced by the platform, no exceptions without Credit Committee approval.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Rule", "Threshold", "Why"], ["Max facility per customer", "15% of declared annual revenue", "Prevents over-leverage regardless of score"], ["Min monthly repayment", "5% of drawn balance", "Stops debt compounding silently"], ["Annual clean-down", "Drawn = 0 for 30 consecutive days every 12 months", "Confirms the facility is working capital, not term debt in disguise"], ["Utilisation soft cap", "Above 85% for more than 60 consecutive days", "EWS trigger; signals undersized facility or distress"], ["Sector concentration", "25% of total book per sector", "Prevents portfolio shock from sectoral downturn"], ["Single buyer or anchor", "5% per buyer; 25% per anchor", "Idiosyncratic risk control"], ["Single product line", "50% of book in any one product", "Diversification across product lines"], ["DSCR floor", "1.20x trailing 12 months", "Ensures borrower can service the new facility"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.10 Risk Segmentation by Probability of Default", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-10-risk-segmentation-by-probability-of-default", "text": "C.10 Risk Segmentation by Probability of Default"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Customers are segmented into four tiers at underwriting and re-segmented quarterly. Each tier carries a clear product action. Re-segmentation is automatic; downgrades trigger limit reviews; upgrades trigger pre-approved upsells.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Tier", "PD Range", "Profile", "Product Action"], ["Prime", "0 to 3%", "Strong bureau, 2+ years, consistent cash flows", "All variants eligible; lowest pricing; pre-approved upsells; auto limit increase"], ["Standard", "3 to 8%", "Adequate bureau, some volatility", "Standard pricing; standard monitoring; quarterly review"], ["Near-Prime", "8 to 15%", "Thin bureau, younger business, sector risk", "Higher pricing; more frequent review; lower max limit; collateral preferred; EDB guarantee co-applied where eligible"], ["Elevated", "Above 15%", "Multiple delinquency signals", "Decline or manual-only review; no auto-products; credit committee for any approval"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.11 KPI Framework", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-11-kpi-framework", "text": "C.11 KPI Framework"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "A balanced scorecard across five categories. Tracked weekly, reported monthly, reviewed quarterly at board level. Metrics evolve as the book scales: in Year 1, funnel and approval metrics dominate; in Year 3, portfolio efficiency and trust metrics dominate.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Funnel Metrics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "funnel-metrics", "text": "Funnel Metrics"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Definition", "Year 1 Target", "Year 3 Target"], ["Eligibility rate", "% of account holders meeting pre-qual threshold", "35%", "50%"], ["Application rate", "% of pre-qualified who apply", "25%", "35%"], ["Approval rate", "% of applicants approved", "40 to 45%", "55%"], ["Acceptance rate", "% of approved who accept offer", "75%", "80%"], ["First draw rate", "% of accepted who draw within 30 days", "90%", "92%"], ["Time to offer (Express)", "Application to offer", "Under 4 hours", "Under 2 hours"], ["Time to offer (Standard)", "Application to offer", "Under 72 hours", "Under 48 hours"], ["Time to disburse", "Acceptance to funds in account", "Under 30 seconds", "Under 15 seconds"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Portfolio Health", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "portfolio-health", "text": "Portfolio Health"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Year 1 Target", "Year 3 Target"], ["Average utilisation rate", "45 to 55%", "50 to 60%"], ["PAR 30+ (overdue more than 30 days)", "Under 4%", "Under 3%"], ["NPL rate", "Under 2.5%", "Under 2%"], ["Net credit loss rate", "Under 3.5%", "Under 2.5%"], ["Recovery rate", "Above 40%", "Above 50%"], ["Clean-down compliance", "Above 75%", "Above 85%"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "AI Performance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "ai-performance", "text": "AI Performance"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Target"], ["Model Gini coefficient", "Above 0.55"], ["PSI (Population Stability Index)", "Below 0.25 (stable)"], ["Predicted versus actual default delta", "Within plus or minus 20%"], ["Human override rate", "Below 15% (signals model is trusted)"], ["EWS hit rate (correct predictions)", "Above 65%"], ["EWS false positive rate", "Below 25%"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Speed and Customer Experience", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "speed-and-customer-experience", "text": "Speed and Customer Experience"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Target"], ["App NPS for lending", "Above 65"], ["Application completion rate", "Above 85%"], ["Complaint rate (lending)", "Below 0.5% of active facilities per month"], ["Re-application rate after decline", "Above 30% within 90 days (signals perceived fairness)"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Customer Trust and Stickiness", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "customer-trust-and-stickiness", "text": "Customer Trust and Stickiness"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Target"], ["Repeat draw rate", "Above 60% of facilities with more than 3 draws in 12 months"], ["Facility renewal rate", "Above 70% at 12-month anniversary"], ["Referral rate", "Above 15% referred another SME"], ["Auto-repayment opt-in rate", "Above 40%"], ["Data consent retention at renewal", "Above 80%"]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.12 Decision-Making Playbook", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-12-decision-making-playbook", "text": "C.12 Decision-Making Playbook"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Five scenarios that come up in every SME lending operation. The playbook is what good Heads of Product do reflexively, written down so the team can do it before the operator needs to be in the room.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Scenario 1: Approval rates rise; losses spike", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "scenario-1-approval-rates-rise-losses-spike", "text": "Scenario 1: Approval rates rise; losses spike"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Diagnose before acting. Is it a model failure, a macro shock, or a fraud breakout? Different responses.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Day 1 to Day 7:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Moratorium on auto-approve for the highest-risk cohort.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cohort analysis: which vintage, segment, tier is defaulting? Concentrated or broad?", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Model PSI check: has the scoring model drifted?", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Compare actual versus predicted PD by cohort.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "If model failure: pause AI auto-approval, revert to rules-only, retrain the model on updated data, escalate to Model Risk Committee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "If macro shock: do not over-tighten (will deny future good customers). Deploy enhanced monitoring on at-risk sectors. Increase provisioning. Outreach to customers showing early stress.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "If fraud breakout: lock down the typology, sweep for related-account exposure, file SARs, brief Compliance and CRO.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Communication: brief CRO and CEO within 24 hours. Board pack with root-cause analysis within two weeks. Never hide a portfolio problem.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Scenario 2: Customers do not understand declines", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "scenario-2-customers-do-not-understand-declines", "text": "Scenario 2: Customers do not understand declines"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This is a product failure and a trust failure, not a credit policy problem.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Audit decline reason codes: are they generic (\"insufficient history\") or specific (\"your business is 9 months old, we require 12+\")? Specificity is the fix.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Redesign the decline experience with a UX writer. Translate SHAP outputs into human language.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Add actionable next steps to every decline.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Implement automatic re-evaluation at 90 days with proactive notification.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Make the right to human review prominently visible, not buried in T&Cs.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Long-term: build the Credit Builder feature in the app.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Scenario 3: Regulator questions AI explainability", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "scenario-3-regulator-questions-ai-explainability", "text": "Scenario 3: Regulator questions AI explainability"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Welcome it. It means we take it seriously enough to scrutinise.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Immediate response package:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Model documentation: full technical description, training data, validation, performance metrics (Gini, KS, AUC).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Decision audit trail: for any specific customer, produce the exact SHAP contribution of every feature.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Fairness audit: sector and emirate-level approval parity analysis.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Human oversight evidence: log of all human overrides.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Live demo: show how SHAP values translate to customer-facing reason codes.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Proactive: offer quarterly AI model governance reports to the regulator before they ask. Build the relationship before we need it. CBUAE's AI/ML guidance note (2024) established five principles: governance, fairness, transparency, human oversight, data management. We should already be compliant.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Scenario 4: Engineering wants to slow launches due to risk", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "scenario-4-engineering-wants-to-slow-launches-due-", "text": "Scenario 4: Engineering wants to slow launches due to risk"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Understand the specific risk: technical debt, data quality, compliance gap, or capacity? Each has a different answer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Map to impact: which risks would cause customer harm or regulatory breach? Those are blockers. Which are manageable with mitigating controls? Those allow launch with guardrails.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Propose tiered launch: \"Closed beta to 500 customers. Monitor 30 days. Expand only if metrics within policy.\"", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Negotiate what to defer. Ship the core facility first; defer the Dynamic Limit Booster and exotic add-ons.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The principle: product velocity matters, but a broken lending product causes real harm to customers (financial damage) and to the bank (reputational, regulatory). A simpler product launched well beats a complex product launched poorly.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Scenario 5: CEO asks to double volume in 6 months", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "scenario-5-ceo-asks-to-double-volume-in-6-months", "text": "Scenario 5: CEO asks to double volume in 6 months"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "First question back: where does the growth come from? Higher approval rates, larger limits, new segments, or better funnel conversion? The answer determines the risk profile.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The safe path to 2x:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Funnel optimisation (lowest risk). If acceptance rate is 75%, what is driving the 25% drop-off? Fix the funnel first; add volume without changing credit standards.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Pre-qualification expansion. Automate more proactive outreach to eligible existing customers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Limit increases for performing customers. Dynamic limit increases for the top 20% of portfolio by performance. Existing customers carry lower marginal risk.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Segment expansion. Accelerate Tier 2 launch with appropriate guardrails.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "What to resist:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Dropping credit floors below policy minimums to hit a number.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Expanding to segments without sufficient data.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Removing the human review layer for Standard or Enhanced tiers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "C.13 Putting It All Together", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "c-13-putting-it-all-together", "text": "C.13 Putting It All Together"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Eight rules sit at the centre of this appendix. They are the operating beliefs that should carry through every product decision.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Pricing is risk-based and centred on portfolio NIM, never flat. Some customers price below NIM, some above; the book hits the target.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Decisions are deterministic where the regulator demands it and AI-driven where the data is rich. Both layers run in every application.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every AI decision is explainable to the customer in plain Arabic and English, and to the regulator in SHAP feature contributions.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Monitoring beats collections. Early Warning is the largest single source of value protection in the operation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Collections is personalised by channel, time, and tone. A linear cadence wastes effort on the easy cases and misses the hard ones.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Declined customers are not lost customers. The Credit Builder turns 50 to 60 percent of declines into future revenue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The funnel tapers at the beginning, not the end. Eliminating early respects the customer's time and ours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Every concession, override, and exception is logged, reviewed, and fed back into the model. The system learns from every human decision.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h1", "spans": [{"t": "Appendix D: EDB-Guaranteed SME Term Lending: Distribution Model with FLDG", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "appendix-d-edb-guaranteed-sme-term-lending-distrib", "text": "Appendix D: EDB-Guaranteed SME Term Lending: Distribution Model with FLDG"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The three balance-sheet products in the main body cover the whitespace where the platform funds the customer directly. There is a separate, equally large opportunity that does not need the platform's balance sheet at all: distributing EDB-guaranteed SME term loans on behalf of a Partner Bank, taking origination and servicing fees, and providing a First Loss Default Guarantee (FLDG) to share the credit risk.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This appendix sets out the mechanics, the partner bank selection, the FLDG capital structure, the integration into the platform's decision engine, and the three-year unit economics. Net of FLDG, this product delivers AED 30 million of net contribution by Year 3 on AED 2 billion of disbursement, using AED 100 million of FLDG capital. Return on FLDG capital reaches 30 percent by Year 3.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.1 Why a Distribution Model Sits Alongside the Three Core Products", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-1-why-a-distribution-model-sits-alongside-the-th", "text": "D.1 Why a Distribution Model Sits Alongside the Three Core Products"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Pathway B from the planning analysis (see preceding section). The platform is not a CBUAE-licensed bank or finance company. It cannot directly be a Partner Bank under the EDB Credit Guarantee Scheme. But it can sit alongside one of the 13 Partner Banks, source the customer, run preliminary decisioning, service the loan, and provide an FLDG to make the bank willing to underwrite tickets the bank's own sales team would not pursue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This pathway gives the platform four things at once.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Bank-cost funding. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Customer rate is capped at 3M EIBOR + 5% (around 9 to 10% all-in today). The platform itself funds at SOFR + 5% on a USD warehouse, equivalent to 9 to 12% locally. Without the bank, this segment is uneconomic for the platform. With the bank, the platform earns fees on a book funded by deposits.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Capital efficiency. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Platform commits FLDG capital (roughly 8% of disbursement) instead of full equity-and-warehouse funding (typically 8 to 12% equity plus mezz on top of senior warehouse). FLDG capital is leveraged 12.5 to 1 against disbursement; balance-sheet products at 8 to 10 to 1.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Customer ownership. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "Even though the loan sits on the bank's balance sheet, the customer relationship sits on the platform. The platform owns the app, the data, the servicing, the cross-sell. The customer does not interact with the bank's brand at any stage.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": [{"t": "Path to scale without a CBUAE Finance Company licence. ", "b": true, "i": false}, {"t": "The Pathway A licence track takes 12 to 24 months. Pathway B can be live within 6 months. The platform builds a track record and scale; it can apply for its own licence later from a position of strength.", "b": false, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.2 The Structure: Roles and Money Flow", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-2-the-structure-roles-and-money-flow", "text": "D.2 The Structure: Roles and Money Flow"}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Four-Party Diagram", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "four-party-diagram", "text": "Four-Party Diagram"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["SME Customer", "Platform", "Partner Bank", "EDB"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": [{"t": "↓   Master Distribution Agreement + Servicing Agreement + FLDG Agreement   ↓", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["EDB Credit Guarantee Scheme: 50% of any loss above FLDG"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Roles", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "roles", "text": "Roles"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Party", "Role"], ["SME Customer", "Borrower of record. Pays the bank monthly via auto-debit through platform app."], ["Platform", "Customer acquisition; preliminary decisioning; servicing; collections (Day 1 to Day 30); FLDG provider; data integration."], ["Partner Bank", "Lender of record. Final credit approval per its own policy. Books the loan on its balance sheet. Holds capital. Applies for and receives EDB guarantee."], ["EDB", "Guarantor for 50% of any loss after FLDG is exhausted. Pays guarantee fee invoice; receives guarantee fee from bank (passed through to customer)."]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Money Flow", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "money-flow", "text": "Money Flow"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Step", "Cash Movement"], ["1. Onboarding", "SME signs facility agreement with bank (digital). Platform onboards customer to its app. FLDG cash collateral posted by platform to bank's lien account."], ["2. Disbursement", "Bank disburses loan to customer. Bank pays platform an origination fee (1.5 to 2.5% of disbursement)."], ["3. Repayment", "Customer pays monthly EMI to bank via platform-managed auto-debit. Bank pays platform a servicing fee monthly (1.5 to 2.0% per annum on outstanding book)."], ["4. Default", "If customer misses a payment: platform handles Day 1 to Day 30 collections. From Day 30, joint collections with bank. Loss recognition follows IFRS 9 staging."], ["5. Loss event", "On charge-off: bank claims FLDG from platform's cash collateral. If FLDG is exhausted, bank claims 50% of remaining loss from EDB. Residual sits on the bank's books."], ["6. FLDG release", "As loans amortise and run off without default, FLDG cash collateral is progressively released back to the platform per the agreed schedule."]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.3 Risk Waterfall and FLDG Mechanics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-3-risk-waterfall-and-fldg-mechanics", "text": "D.3 Risk Waterfall and FLDG Mechanics"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Three layers of loss absorption sit between an SME defaulting and the partner bank taking a loss on its books.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Loss Absorption Waterfall on a Default"]]}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Tier 1: FLDG (Platform)", "Tier 2: EDB Guarantee", "Tier 3: Partner Bank"]]}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Tier", "Coverage", "Source"], ["Tier 1: FLDG", "First 8% of disbursement loss (configurable 5 to 10%)", "Platform cash collateral at the bank, lien-marked"], ["Tier 2: EDB Guarantee", "50% of any loss above FLDG, capped at AED 10M per SME", "EDB CGS"], ["Tier 3: Partner Bank", "Remaining 50% above FLDG (residual)", "Bank's own credit reserve"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Worked Example", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "worked-example", "text": "Worked Example"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Assume AED 100M of disbursement to a cohort of SMEs.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Loss Scenario", "Total Loss", "FLDG Pays", "EDB Pays", "Bank Pays"], ["Expected (1.5%)", "AED 1.5M", "AED 1.5M", "AED 0", "AED 0"], ["Stressed (5%)", "AED 5.0M", "AED 5.0M", "AED 0", "AED 0"], ["Severe (10%)", "AED 10.0M", "AED 8.0M", "AED 1.0M", "AED 1.0M"], ["Catastrophic (20%)", "AED 20.0M", "AED 8.0M", "AED 6.0M", "AED 6.0M"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "At expected loss levels (1 to 2.5% on EDB-eligible SMEs in priority sectors), the FLDG is the only layer that pays. The EDB guarantee is unused but retained as tail-risk protection. The bank takes essentially zero credit cost.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This is why Partner Banks are willing to deploy capital and balance sheet on this product. They earn the spread between cost of funds and the platform-paid servicing fee, with the platform absorbing all expected losses through FLDG and EDB absorbing tail risk.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "FLDG Capital Form", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "fldg-capital-form", "text": "FLDG Capital Form"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Cash collateral is the simplest and most accepted form. Other forms are available but each has friction.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["FLDG Form", "Bank Acceptance", "Cost to Platform", "Friction"], ["Cash collateral (preferred)", "High; lien-marked at the partner bank", "Foregone yield: 15% cost of equity less 3% deposit rate = 12% per annum", "Simple; standard"], ["Bank guarantee from another bank", "Medium; depends on issuing bank's rating", "Bank guarantee fee: 1.5 to 2.5% per annum", "Two banks involved; counterparty review"], ["Credit insurance (Atradius, Coface, Euler Hermes)", "Low to Medium; bank dependent", "Premium 1.5 to 3.5% per annum on insured limit", "Insurer underwrites the platform; capacity caps"], ["Reinsurance wrapper via Sharia takaful operator", "Low at first; building", "Comparable to credit insurance", "Sharia structure adds complexity"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Recommendation: cash collateral for Year 1 to Year 2 to remove every friction with the first partner banks. Move to a hybrid (60% cash, 40% credit insurance) in Year 3 once volumes justify the insurer underwrite and once internal track record reduces the cash collateral demanded by banks.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.4 Partner Bank Selection", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-4-partner-bank-selection", "text": "D.4 Partner Bank Selection"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Of the 13 EDB Partner Banks, four are realistic first partners based on fintech-friendliness, SME book appetite, and operational readiness.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Bank", "Why First-Wave Candidate", "Risk in Choosing"], ["RAKBank", "Long-time SME specialist; existing fintech partnerships; willing to co-build", "Mid-sized; concentration risk if it dominates the book"], ["Mashreq", "NeoBiz fintech-forward; embedded lending platform; tech-friendly", "Larger SME book may compete with platform's own"], ["ADCB", "Procash and BusinessEdge programs; first EDB partner Dec 2022; active growth", "Slower decision cycles than fintechs are used to"], ["ADIB", "Sharia-compliant; EDB partnership Oct 2024; growing SME push", "Sharia-only path; conventional needs second bank"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Recommendation: sign first MoU with RAKBank (conventional product, fastest path), second with ADIB (Sharia variant), third with Mashreq or ADCB by end of Year 2. Three partners by Year 3 is enough for resilience without operational overload. No single bank above 50% of distribution book.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Master Distribution Agreement Terms", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "master-distribution-agreement-terms", "text": "Master Distribution Agreement Terms"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Exclusive distribution territory: defined by sector and ticket band, not full exclusivity. Platform retains the right to distribute to other banks in non-overlapping segments.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "FLDG amount: 8% of disbursement (configurable Tier-by-Tier per the EDB checklist).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Origination fee: 1.5 to 2.5% of disbursement, paid at disbursement.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Servicing fee: 1.75 to 2.0% per annum on outstanding book, paid monthly in arrears.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cross-sell rights: bank cannot offer competing platform products (account, payments, BNPL) to platform-sourced customers without platform consent. Platform cannot poach bank's existing SME customers.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Service levels: platform's preliminary decisioning must achieve under 24-hour turnaround; bank's final approval within 48 hours; total under 72 hours.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Termination: 12-month notice on either side; existing book runs to maturity under the original terms.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Audit and reporting: monthly performance pack to bank; quarterly model performance review; annual joint EDB review.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.5 The EDB Eligibility Layer", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-5-the-edb-eligibility-layer", "text": "D.5 The EDB Eligibility Layer"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Every loan distributed under this model must pass the EDB Credit Guarantee Scheme checklist. The platform's decision engine must include a parallel CGS-eligibility screen at Stage 3 (see Appendix C.3).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Three Eligibility Lanes", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "three-eligibility-lanes", "text": "Three Eligibility Lanes"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Each application is scored against three lanes simultaneously.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Lane", "Outcome", "Approval"], ["CGS Policy", "Fits all 33 parameters with no deviation. Standard CGS pricing and tenor.", "Bank's own delegated authority for the relationship manager"], ["CGS Deviation 1", "One or two parameters in the Deviation 1 column. Mid-level approval.", "Bank's CGS Credit Manager"], ["CGS Deviation 2", "Parameters in Deviation 2 column. Head of Credit at the bank.", "Bank's HOC"], ["Beyond Deviation 2", "Treated as high-level deviation; route to MCIC at the bank or decline.", "MCIC at the bank"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "The 33-Row Eligibility Checklist (Reproduced)", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "the-33-row-eligibility-checklist-reproduced", "text": "The 33-Row Eligibility Checklist (Reproduced)"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "All 33 parameters of the EDB Credit Guarantee Scheme as captured in the official document, mapped against the three lanes above. The decision engine encodes every line as a deterministic gate; all gates must pass at the chosen lane for the loan to be CGS-eligible.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Sr.", "Parameter", "Policy", "Deviation 1", "Deviation 2"], ["1", "Eligible borrower", "SMEs located and operating in UAE", "NA", "NA"], ["2", "Eligible sectors", "UAE National owned: all except Tier 4 (PG required); Expat owned: Priority Sector Tier 1 only", "Expat in Priority Tier 2", "n/a"], ["3", "Ineligible borrower", "Outside UAE; speculative; financial services; passive investment; prohibited / blacklisted; Tier 4", "NA", "NA"], ["4", "Segment definition", "Micro <30M; SME <250M; Start-up 6 to 12 months (UAE National only)", "n/a", "n/a"], ["5", "Collateral", "PG of all partners ex UAE National sponsor; assets registered with EIRC; undated cheque or PN unless RE mortgage", "Partners <20% may not provide PG with justification", "n/a"], ["6", "Use of funds", "Asset purchase / construction / business expansion / inventory / salary and rent (services) / opex", "NA", "NA"], ["7", "Loan type", "Term loan + WC revolving; OD up to 5% or AED 1M; buyout <20% for RE access; no restructured", "OD up to 10% or AED 1.5M; buyout <30%", "Guarantees max 10% of program limit"], ["8", "Guarantee amount", "Micro AED 2.49M / 50%; SME AED 10M / 50%; Start-up AED 500K / 50% (max ticket AED 1M)", "n/a", "n/a"], ["9", "Pricing cap and fee", "Up to AED 2.49M: 3M EIBOR + 6%, 3% + VAT fee; AED 2.5 to 4.99M: + 5%, 2% + VAT; AED 5M+: + 5%, 1.5% + VAT", "n/a", "n/a"], ["10", "Maximum maturity (term loan)", "SME 7 yr; Micro 5 yr; Start-up 4 yr", "+1 yr", "+2 yr"], ["11", "Repayment term", "TL: max 3 months (quarterly); WC: max 180 days", "WC: +30 days", "n/a"], ["12", "Grace period (term loan)", "Max 6 months one-off, principal only", "+3 months", "+6 months"], ["13", "LOB for established business", "Min 3+ years", "3 years", "<2 years"], ["14", "Management experience", "Same line of business >3 years", "3 years", "<2 years"], ["15", "Nationalities", "All but no sensitive nationalities; resident sensitive nationals require EDB compliance screen", "n/a", "n/a"], ["16", "Age of owners / partners", "25 to 65 at maturity; >65 with succession plan", "n/a", "n/a"], ["17", "CBRB", "Performing / Normal for borrower, owners, signatories, guarantors, group", "n/a", "n/a"], ["18", "AECB delinquency history", "Nil overdue; max 2x <30 DPD in 12M; max 1x 30 to 60 DPD in 24M; never 90+ DPD in 5 yr", "+1 instance", "+1 instance"], ["19", "Court cases", "No active court cases except labour <AED 100K; no closed in last 3 months except labour <AED 100K", "Approve with justification", "n/a"], ["20", "Returned cheques", "Max 2 in 12 months per party; payment proof for bounced cheques", "+1 cheque", "+1 cheque"], ["21", "Max credit exposure", "Micro AED 15M; SME AED 75M; Micro: max with 3 banks + lender", "+2 banks", "n/a"], ["22", "Audited financials", "3 years audited + latest in-house (except start-ups)", "2 years audited", "n/a"], ["23", "Approved credit proposal", "Lender approval not older than 30 calendar days at submission", "+30 days", "n/a"], ["24", "Bank statements + VAT", "If auditor not listed with PB, 6 months bank statements + VAT to be obtained and verified", "n/a", "n/a"], ["25", "Minimum annual turnover", "AED 2M services; AED 3.5M manufacturing", "n/a", "n/a"], ["26", "Sales / revenue growth", "Positive in last 12 months", "Negative <10% (subject to positive NP)", "Negative <20% (subject to positive NP)"], ["27", "OPM (EBITDA)", ">8%", "OPM <8% but >6%", "OPM <5.99% but >5%"], ["28", "Current ratio", ">1.25", "1.24 to 1.20", "1.19 to 1.15"], ["29", "DSCR (incl. proposed)", ">1.35x", "1.34 to 1.25", "1.25 to 1.15"], ["30", "Adjusted leverage", "UAE-N non-priority <1.0x; Priority <2.0x", "+0.25x higher", "+0.25x higher"], ["31", "Receivables concentration", "<=40% (start-ups <=60%); Govt / Semi-Govt up to 60%", "100% for GREs (UAE-N owned)", "100% for GREs"], ["32", "Inventory turnover", "UAE-N non-priority <120 days; Priority <180 days", "+30 days", "+30 days"], ["33", "Receivables turnover", "<180 days", "+30 days", "+30 days"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "All deviations require Credit Forum approval at the platform level before submission to the bank. Cases that meet only Deviation 2 are scored separately at quarterly portfolio reviews to ensure they do not exceed 25 percent of the book.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.6 Customer Journey", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-6-customer-journey", "text": "D.6 Customer Journey"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "From the customer perspective, the experience is identical to the three core products: app-driven, fast, transparent. Behind the scenes, the orchestration sits between platform and partner bank.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "End-to-End Steps", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "end-to-end-steps", "text": "End-to-End Steps"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Step", "Customer Sees", "Behind the Scenes"], ["Application start", "Tap to apply for a term loan in the platform app. Choose tenor and amount.", "Platform UI; CGS lane selector live"], ["Identity and consent", "UAE Pass auth. One consent screen for AECB, Lean, FTA.", "Platform pulls KYB, AECB, OF data; auto-fills application"], ["Preliminary decisioning", "\"You may be eligible for AED X at Y% over Z years.\"", "Platform decision engine runs 33-row CGS check + own scorecard; under 4 hours"], ["Bank submission", "\"We are confirming your offer with our partner bank. ETA 24 to 48 hours.\"", "Platform packages credit memo and submits to bank's CGS portal"], ["Bank approval", "Final offer in app: rate, tenor, EMI, total cost.", "Bank approves under its delegated authority; EDB guarantee approval is parallel and behind the scenes"], ["Acceptance", "Digital signature via UAE Pass. Single bank facility agreement.", "FLDG cash collateral posted at the bank against this loan"], ["Disbursement", "Funds in account in under 24 hours.", "Bank disburses; platform receives origination fee"], ["Servicing", "Monthly EMI auto-debited; in-app dashboard; chat support.", "Platform manages servicing; bank's books update from servicing feed"], ["Repayment / closure", "Final EMI; account closure; option for top-up.", "FLDG released back to platform per amortisation schedule"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "What the Customer Does Not See", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "what-the-customer-does-not-see", "text": "What the Customer Does Not See"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Which bank books the loan. The platform brand fronts every interaction; the bank brand appears only on the formal facility agreement (regulatory disclosure).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The CGS eligibility lane the loan falls into. The customer sees one offer with terms; the lane is internal.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The FLDG. This is a platform-bank arrangement; not disclosed to the customer beyond standard fee transparency.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "The EDB guarantee. EDB's role is in the agreement footer; not surfaced in the offer.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.7 FLDG Capital Structure and Governance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-7-fldg-capital-structure-and-governance", "text": "D.7 FLDG Capital Structure and Governance"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "FLDG capital is held as cash collateral in a lien-marked account at each Partner Bank. Sized to disbursement, not outstanding book; releases as loans amortise.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Sizing Logic", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "sizing-logic", "text": "Sizing Logic"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Base FLDG: 8% of cumulative disbursement, less amortised principal.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Tiered overlay: an extra 2% on Deviation 2 loans (cap at 25% of book).", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Catastrophe buffer: 1% additional held in a parent platform account, not lien-marked, for emergency top-up if a single Partner Bank's lien account approaches exhaustion.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Gross FLDG capital required (Year 3): 8% of AED 2,000M disbursement plus overlays = approximately AED 175M nominal, of which AED 100M is the typical running balance after amortisation.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Capital Form Mix Over Time", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "capital-form-mix-over-time", "text": "Capital Form Mix Over Time"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Year", "Cash Collateral", "Credit Insurance", "Total FLDG Outstanding"], ["Year 1", "100%", "0%", "AED 12M"], ["Year 2", "80%", "20%", "AED 50M"], ["Year 3", "60%", "40%", "AED 100M"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Governance", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "governance", "text": "Governance"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "FLDG Investment Committee: monthly review of FLDG balance, calls, releases, and forward sizing.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Independent reconciliation: monthly tri-party reconciliation between platform, bank, and a third-party trustee.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Stress tests: quarterly scenarios at 2x, 4x, and 8x expected loss; pre-funded backstop facility from a parent or mezz lender.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Bank exposure caps: no Partner Bank above 50% of total FLDG; no single sector above 25% of FLDG; no single borrower above AED 5M of FLDG.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Audit trail: every FLDG draw triggers an immediate notification to ops, finance, and CRO with the underlying loan, the trigger event, and the projected ultimate loss.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.8 Three-Year Unit Economics", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-8-three-year-unit-economics", "text": "D.8 Three-Year Unit Economics"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Built up from disbursement assumptions, fees, FLDG cost of carry, expected losses absorbed under the FLDG, and operating costs.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Volume and Book Build", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "volume-and-book-build", "text": "Volume and Book Build"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Driver", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "200", "800", "2,000"], ["Average tenor (months)", "48", "48", "48"], ["Average ticket (AED)", "1,500,000", "1,500,000", "1,500,000"], ["Number of loans booked", "133", "533", "1,333"], ["Active live loans (year-end)", "133", "600", "1,700"], ["Average outstanding book (AED M)", "90", "500", "1,400"], ["FLDG outstanding (AED M, year-end average)", "12", "50", "140"], ["Partner banks live", "1", "2", "3"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Revenue Build", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "revenue-build", "text": "Revenue Build"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Revenue Line", "Year 1 (AED M)", "Year 2 (AED M)", "Year 3 (AED M)"], ["Origination fee (2.0% of disbursement)", "4.0", "16.0", "40.0"], ["Servicing fee (2.0% pa on avg book)", "1.8", "10.0", "28.0"], ["Cash collateral interest (3.0% pa on FLDG)", "0.4", "1.2", "3.0"], ["Total revenue", "6.2", "27.2", "71.0"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Cost Build", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "cost-build", "text": "Cost Build"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Cost Line", "Year 1 (AED M)", "Year 2 (AED M)", "Year 3 (AED M)"], ["Credit losses absorbed (FLDG)", "0.9", "7.5", "21.0"], ["FLDG cost of carry (12% spread on cash collateral)", "1.2", "4.5", "12.6"], ["Operating cost (allocated)", "2.5", "5.0", "11.0"], ["Bank-side ops integration cost", "0.5", "0.7", "1.0"], ["Total cost", "5.1", "17.7", "45.6"]]}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Profitability and Capital Returns", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "profitability-and-capital-returns", "text": "Profitability and Capital Returns"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Year 1", "Year 2", "Year 3"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "1.1", "9.5", "25.4"], ["Net contribution as % of disbursement", "0.5%", "1.2%", "1.3%"], ["FLDG capital deployed (avg, AED M)", "8", "32", "100"], ["Return on FLDG capital", "14%", "30%", "25%"], ["Return on book (book ROA equivalent)", "1.2%", "1.9%", "1.8%"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Key reads:", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Year 1 is light because volumes ramp slowly while operating cost is front-loaded.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Year 2 is the inflection. Origination fee scales linearly with disbursement; servicing fee scales with the carry book; FLDG cost of carry stays manageable.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Year 3 net contribution of AED 25.4M is on AED 100M of FLDG capital. Return on FLDG capital of 25 to 30% is materially better than balance-sheet products on the same capital base.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Cumulative three-year net contribution: AED 36M against AED 3 billion of disbursement and a peak FLDG of AED 140M.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Sensitivity Analysis", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "sensitivity-analysis", "text": "Sensitivity Analysis"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Three sensitivities matter most. Base case is the table above.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Scenario", "Trigger", "Year 3 Net Contribution Impact"], ["Base", "Loss rate 1.5%; origination 2%; servicing 2%", "AED 25.4M"], ["Stressed losses", "Loss rate to 3%", "Down AED 21M; Year 3 net AED 4.4M"], ["Lower fees", "Origination to 1.5%; servicing to 1.5%", "Down AED 17M; Year 3 net AED 8.4M"], ["FLDG to 5%", "Lower FLDG share by 3 percentage points; loss exposure preserved", "Up AED 4M; Year 3 net AED 29.4M; bank may resist"], ["EDB pricing cap softens", "Customer rate up 100 bps; servicing fee up 50 bps", "Up AED 7M; Year 3 net AED 32.4M"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The two biggest economic levers are loss performance and the negotiated fee split with the partner bank. Both are owned by the platform: losses by underwriting quality, fee split by negotiation leverage and track record.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.9 Capital Efficiency Compared to Balance-Sheet Products", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-9-capital-efficiency-compared-to-balance-sheet-p", "text": "D.9 Capital Efficiency Compared to Balance-Sheet Products"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "This is the strategic argument for adding the distribution model. It is materially more capital-efficient than the three core products.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Metric (Year 3)", "Product 1 (Smart Invoice + BNPL)", "Product 2 (Healthcare Receivables)", "Product 3 (Anchor SCF)", "Product 4 (Distribution + FLDG)"], ["Disbursement (AED M)", "3,500", "2,500", "4,000", "2,000"], ["Average book (AED M)", "1,400", "850", "1,200", "1,400"], ["Net contribution (AED M)", "63", "25.5", "30", "25.4"], ["Capital required (equity + warehouse) (AED M)", "180", "110", "140", "100 (FLDG only)"], ["Return on capital", "35%", "23%", "21%", "25%"], ["Capital intensity (cap as % of book)", "13%", "13%", "12%", "7%"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The distribution model (Product 4) sits at the highest capital efficiency by design. It also gives the platform exposure to a customer segment (term lending in priority sectors at bank-level pricing) that none of the three balance-sheet products would otherwise reach economically.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "In a stressed scenario where the platform's senior warehouse lines tighten or pricing widens, Product 4 economics are materially less affected than the three balance-sheet products. This is portfolio insurance, not just incremental revenue.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.10 Risks and Mitigants", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-10-risks-and-mitigants", "text": "D.10 Risks and Mitigants"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Risk", "Description", "Mitigant"], ["Partner bank concentration", "First partner accounts for over 50% of disbursement and FLDG.", "Hard cap of 50% per bank; second partner live by Q4 Year 1; third by Year 2."], ["Bank pulls partnership", "Strategic shift, internal credit policy change, leadership change at the bank.", "12-month notice in MoU; existing book runs to maturity; second and third partners as natural backup."], ["FLDG triggered above expected level", "Loss rate breaches 8% on a cohort, exhausting FLDG.", "Tight underwriting + Credit Forum sign-off on Deviation 2 loans; portfolio stress tested quarterly; backstop facility pre-arranged with mezz lender."], ["CBUAE FLDG guidance shift", "CBUAE publishes formal FLDG guidance restricting structure or capital treatment.", "Quarterly engagement with CBUAE; structure aligned to global precedents (RBI India, BoT Thailand); product designed with regulatory headroom."], ["Cross-sell conflict with bank", "Bank tries to sell its own products to platform-sourced customers.", "Non-compete clause in MoU; quarterly review of customer-touch logs; trigger termination clause if breached."], ["EDB guarantee refused on a specific loan", "EDB declines a particular submission post-deviation review.", "Pre-screening at platform level using full 33-row checklist; pre-clearance protocol with EDB CGS team for borderline cases."], ["Bank's final approval rate drops", "Bank's credit committee starts declining a higher percentage of platform-submitted files.", "Joint quarterly portfolio review; align platform's preliminary scoring to the bank's policy; co-build the model with bank credit team."], ["Operational integration breakdown", "Platform data feeds and bank's core banking system fall out of sync.", "Daily reconciliation; weekly ops huddle; SLA monitoring; mutually-agreed reconciliation breaks process."], ["FLDG cash collateral counter-party risk", "Partner bank itself defaults; FLDG cash is at risk.", "Only investment-grade partners; FLDG diversified across 3 partners by Year 3; tri-party trustee for over AED 100M."], ["Customer perception of opaque structure", "Customer feels misled when discovering bank is the lender of record.", "Regulatory disclosure on every offer screen; UAE Pass facility agreement is bank-branded; clear FAQ in app."]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.11 Build Sequence and Milestones", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-11-build-sequence-and-milestones", "text": "D.11 Build Sequence and Milestones"}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Quarter", "Milestone"], ["Q3 2026", "MoU signed with first Partner Bank (RAKBank or ADCB target). Term sheet agreed: FLDG 8%, origination 2%, servicing 2% pa."], ["Q4 2026", "Integration build: API exchange between platform LOS and bank's CGS portal; FLDG cash collateral account opened; legal documents standardised."], ["Q4 2026", "Pilot 50 loans across two priority sectors. End-to-end run with real money. Validate decisioning, EDB approval flow, FLDG mechanics, servicing."], ["Q1 2027", "Production scale to 200 loans. First quarterly portfolio review with bank and EDB."], ["Q1 2027", "Sharia variant live with ADIB as second partner; Sharia FLDG structure (kafalah-based)."], ["Q2 2027", "Third partner bank live (Mashreq target). Conventional and Sharia in parallel."], ["Q3 2027", "Credit insurance wrapper added (Atradius or Coface) to reduce cash collateral burden."], ["Q4 2027", "First annual EDB joint review. Negotiate fee uplift if performance is strong (target 25 bps)."]]}, {"tag": "h2", "spans": [{"t": "D.12 Where This Lands in the Strategy", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "d-12-where-this-lands-in-the-strategy", "text": "D.12 Where This Lands in the Strategy"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The distribution model is the fourth pillar alongside the three balance-sheet products. It is not a substitute. Each pillar serves a different customer need and uses a different capital base.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "table", "rows": [["Pillar", "Customer Need", "Capital", "Margin", "Strategic Role"], ["Product 1: Smart Invoice + BNPL", "Short-cycle working capital, fast", "Equity + warehouse", "High (NIM 10%+)", "Customer acquisition; data engine"], ["Product 2: Healthcare Receivables", "Insurance claim cash conversion", "Equity + Sharia ABS", "Medium (NIM 7%)", "Sector specialist; AUM scale"], ["Product 3: Anchor SCF", "Reverse factoring at scale", "Equity + warehouse", "Low (NIM 4 to 5%)", "Anchor moat; cross-sell hook"], ["Product 4: Distribution + FLDG", "Multi-year term lending at bank rates", "FLDG only", "Thin per dirham; high RoC", "Capital efficiency; bank relationships"]]}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Cross-pillar economics matter. A Product 1 customer who has used invoice discounting for two cycles is a strong candidate for a Product 4 term loan when they move to fund equipment or expansion. A Product 4 customer who has serviced cleanly for 12 months is a target for Product 1 cross-sell.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The four pillars together carry: AED 12 billion of disbursement in Year 3; AED 4.85 billion of average book; AED 144 million of net contribution; AED 530 million of capital deployed (equity, warehouse, FLDG combined). Blended return on capital approaches 27 percent, materially better than any single-pillar plan.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "Integration Points Across the Platform", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "integration-points-across-the-platform", "text": "Integration Points Across the Platform"}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Section 6.2 (Capital Stack) gains a new row: FLDG capital, scaling AED 12M Year 1 to AED 100M Year 3, drawn from equity Tier 1 + ring-fenced cash collateral facility.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Section 6.4 (Build Sequence) gains a parallel track for the Partner Bank MoU and integration.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Appendix C.3 (Decision Engine) gains a CGS-eligibility screen as a parallel branch from Stage 3.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "li", "spans": "Year 3 platform-level economics shift: combined net contribution rises from AED 110M (three balance-sheet products) to AED 144M (four pillars). The marginal AED 34M comes at AED 100M of additional capital, a 34 percent return on the marginal capital.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "h3", "spans": [{"t": "The Strategic Case for Pathway B", "b": true, "i": false}], "lvl": 0, "id": "the-strategic-case-for-pathway-b", "text": "The Strategic Case for Pathway B"}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "Without the distribution model, the platform cannot meaningfully participate in the segment of UAE SME credit that EDB has explicitly chosen to support: term loans in priority sectors at bank pricing. That segment is large (AED 30 billion of EDB-backed lending targeted by 2026), structurally important to government policy, and well-suited to a platform that has the customer relationships but not the bank balance sheet.", "lvl": 0}, {"tag": "p", "spans": "The Pathway B distribution model brings the platform into that segment in 6 to 9 months instead of the 12 to 24 months a Pathway A licence track would take. By the time the platform secures its own CBUAE Finance Company licence, it will already have a track record, a customer base, and a model performance dataset that will accelerate every conversation with EDB and CBUAE.", "lvl": 0}];
